title: delicious homemade ice cream
directions: Open cans of milk and mix together in large bowl.
Mix pudding according to instructions on box.
Mix with other milk and add remainder of milk.
Add vanilla.
Makes 1 gallon.
Tastes like cooked custard without all the work.

title: danish meat patties
directions: Shape into patties and brown in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil. Put with new potatoes.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup of oil until crumbly. Measure out 1 cup and set aside.
Pat remaining mixture lightly into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Stir all ingredients together and boil until candy forms a ball.
Stir well while boiling.
Then pour out on buttered plate and cut into squares to serve.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chicken will have more flavor if you can marinate it in this sauce and then baste chicken with it while grilling.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Melt powdered sugar and chocolate together and cream in butter. Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Add egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Roll package of vanilla wafers fine.
Line pan with crumbs; save some for top.
Pour chocolate mixture over crumbs and let set.
Soften ice cream and spread over set chocolate mixture. Top with remaining crumbs.
Keep frozen; lasts indefinitely.

title: cola roast
directions: Combine salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Rub over surface of roast.
Brown beef roast on all sides in a Dutch oven with vegetable oil.
Drain off drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours or until tender.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown in cooking oil in heavy skillet: beef, sausage, onions and garlic salt.
Put chili mix in.
Mix together rest of ingredients (except spaghetti and tomato/cheese sauce, which you put in last).
Simmer for about 4 hours.
Add spaghetti and tomato/cheese sauce.

title: day ahead scrambled eggs
directions: Mix eggs and milk; soft scramble in butter.
Layer 1/3 egg mixture, 1/3 cheese sauce and 1/3 sausage.
Repeat twice.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Top with mushrooms; cover and bake at 275° for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: noodle candy
directions: Melt butterscotch or Toll House morsels in double boiler.
Pour over noodles and nuts.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: In a glass bowl, layer all ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: curried liver and onions
directions: Tip:
Liver will cut into strips easier if placed on waxed paper lined cookie sheet and put in freezer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gran's stove top beans
directions: Chip
Vienna's
and
onion; add finely chopped bouillon cube. Then
add the rest of the ingredients and mix together. Put on high
to
start and then on low cook for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in shortening about 10 minutes or until tender. Add soy sauce and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add onions. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add bell peppers; cook until tender. Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over steamed rice.
If desired, fresh mushrooms or bean sprouts may be added.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice evenly in bottom of a well-greased oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 the onion soup mix.
Place chicken on rice.
Add rest of soup mix.
Combine mushroom soup and water; blend well and pour over chicken.
Dot with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Add margarine to hot potatoes.
Mix other ingredients; strain. Pour into baking dish or 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until firm.

title: pickled codfish
directions: Soak codfish in water for 5 minutes.
Boil to soften for 5 to 10 minutes, then drain.
Combine the rice, vinegar, water, sugar and oil, then add codfish to this sauce.
Add the onions and tomato.
Chill for 1 hour and serve.

title: jello pineapple salad
directions: Prepare and chill Jell-O, pineapple and pecans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip and softened cream cheese together and spread over Jell-O mixture.
Mix and cook remaining ingredients.
Add lemon juice when thick.
Cool.
Pour over cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle chopped pecans over top.

title: salmon soup
directions: Cook all ingredients about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 1 gallon.

title: almond float
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add milk and almond extract and stir.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice into 1-inch cubes.
Mix cubes in bowl with mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks in their juice.
Store in refrigerator.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Sauce:
Melt margarine. Add flour.
Stir until blended. Slowly add milk and whisk until well blended and thick (use medium/low heat so it doesn't scorch).
Add Cheez Whiz and let cool.
Add sour cream to cooled mixture.

title: watergate salad
directions: In medium bowl, mix all ingredients.
Garnish with remaining 1/2 cup walnuts.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs with wire whisk.
Add sugar, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
Combine pumpkin and whipping cream and stir in the egg mixture.
Pour in 2 deep shell pie crusts and bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° until done.

title: henry's jerky
directions: *Brisket, deer meat, or meat of your choice may be used in place of sirloin.

title: spring rhubarb salad
directions: Combine rhubarb, water and sugar in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until rhubarb is tender.
Remove from heat, add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice and rind.
Chill until syrupy.
Add strawberries.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on lettuce-lined plate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: old-fashioned cream of tomato soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 6 ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Heat cream in the top of a double boiler over simmering water; add to the tomato mixture just before serving. Yield: 8 servings (about 1 1/2 quarts).

title: country fried chicken
directions: For extra spicy chicken increase poultry seasoning to 1/2 teaspoon Deep fry at 365° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: dieter's chili
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bean sprouts and simmer until green pepper is tender.
Add sprouts and heat until warm.
Serves 2.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook chopped squash in salted water until tender.
Drain well. Season with salt, pepper and 1/3 stick oleo.
Add the grated carrot, onion, soup and sour cream.
Melt 1 stick margarine in microwave.
Add to dressing and toss.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples.
Mix dry ingredients with apples.
Fill 9-inch pie shell with mixture.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: cherry s'mores
directions: Place 1 piece of candy on each graham cracker.
Microwave 4 crackers at a time on High, 45 seconds to 1 minute or until chocolate starts to melt.
Pour 1 marshmallow on each side of cracker.
Microwave 15 to 30 seconds until soft.
Top each with a spoonful of cherry pie filling.
Repeat process.
Preparation Time:
3 minutes.
Microwave Time:
4 minutes.

title: sally lunn bread recipe
directions: Butter cookie sheet.
Heat milk and shortening to the temperature of a warm baby bottle.
Mix flour, salt and sugar in a separate bowl.
Add water to yeast in a separate bowl.
Mix the egg in a separate bowl.
Add the warm milk and melted shortening to the bowl of flour, salt and sugar.
Add the egg, yeast and water.
Beat the entire mixture until it comes off the side of the bowl which should be clean.
Cover.
Let rise in a warm (non-air conditioned) place until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Knead the bread down in size and shape into a round loaf.
Place on the cookie sheet and let rise again to half again as big, about 45 minutes.
Bake bread at 300° for approximately 45 minutes.
After 30 minutes, baste the top of the bread with butter and also again after it has finished baking.
Recipe makes one 2 pound loaf.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In small bowl, mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice; let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar mixture to apple slices. Pour apple mixture into pastry-lined pie dish.
Cover with top pastry and crimp edges together.
Vent top.
Bake 45 minutes or until top is golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice steak into very thin strips diagonally.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and ginger; stir in soy sauce.
Pour mixture over meat; stir.
Cut peppers into thin strips and tomatoes into wedges.
Quickly brown meat, one third at a time, in hot oil; remove from pan.
Reduce heat; add peppers, garlic and water to pan and cook until peppers are tender-crisp, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in meat and tomatoes; heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple-nut bread
directions: Mix the oleo, sugar, eggs and salt. Add the flour, apples, nuts, vanilla, sour milk and soda.
Place in greased and floured pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Drain the oranges and pineapple well.
Mix everything all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: manor salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together in a separate bowl.
Mix the ingredients for the dressing.
Just before serving, add the dressing and toss lightly.

title: summer vegetable marinade(appetizer)
directions: Stir oil, vinegar, garlic, salt, pepper and sugar until well blended.
Pour over bite-sized fresh vegetables.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Other vegetables may be substituted, whatever sounds good to you.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Combine above ingredients, beating in eggs one at a time.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Remove and cool 10 minutes.

title: cocoa fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Beat all ingredients in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds and at high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean (oblong, 35 to 40 minutes, layers 30 to 35 minutes and Bundt 40 to 45 minutes).
Cool; frost.

title: nine day pickles
directions: Clean the cucumbers and place in a large glass or crock container.
Mix 1 gallon water and the salt and pour over the cucumbers.
Let stand one week.
Pour off the liquid and split the cukes.
Pour boiling water over the cukes to cover.
Let stand 24 hours and then pour off liquid.
Cover with more boiling water and add alum.
After 24 hours, pour off.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Heat this liquid for three mornings and pour over cukes.
After the third day, place the pickles in sterilized jars and pour heated liquid over them and seal.

title: emerald salad
directions: Mix all except nuts and bacon bits. Mix in nuts just before serving.

title: beet pickles
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put in a gallon jug.
Wash beets; cut top of beets off, leaving about 2-inches on top of beets. Boil beets until tender; thin skin beets while hot.
Bring the spice mixture to a boil.
Pack beets in a quart jar and pour spice mixture over them.
Seal while hot.

title: dianne's marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
(Slice carrots with a food processor if you have one.)
Cook in a small amount of water until just cooked and still firm; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients to form a marinade and pour over the hot carrots.
Let stand overnight or one day in the refrigerator to season.
Store in refrigerator. Serve cold or warm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes until brownness desired.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Refrigerate while preparing remaining ingredients.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl, stirring well.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables; toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Heat the green tomatoes and boil for 15 minutes.
Add Jell-O and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and boil 1 minute.
Seal in jars.

title: snickers bar cookies
directions: Spread cookie dough in a 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake using package directions or until almost golden brown.
Arrange candy over baked layer.
Bake until candy is softened.
Spread evenly over baked layer.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: macaroni and hot dogs
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and sugar.
Simmer for 15 minutes until hot.

title: celery and peas(makes 6 servings)
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water in skillet, add celery, thyme and salt.
Cook until almost tender but still crisp.
Add peas and cook until all is just tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt oleo and bits.
Let cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows. Shape into log in waxed paper.
Roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Slice in 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Boil in salted water until tender. Drain.

title: potato soup with sour cream
directions: Boil peeled potatoes with salt and pepper for about 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and cook on low heat until the potatoes are tender.
Garnish with parsley.

title: spicy vegetable chili
directions: In large saucepan mix soups, water, chili powder, thyme, pepper, zucchini, carrots, chick peas, and black beans.
Over medium heat, heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 40 medium, stir occasionally.
If desired, garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese and fresh parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cut into chunks.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed on box.
Place chicken in greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Mix one can of soup with chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste. Spread stuffing over chicken mixture.
Spread another can of soup over stuffing.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: beef stir fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add beef, stir fry about 2-3 minutes until brown. Gently break apart noodles. Stir noodles, flavor packets, water, bell pepper, broccoli and onion into beef. Boil 3-4 minutes, stirring occasionally until noodles are soft.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine pie mix, 2/3 cup sugar and water in a saucepan.
Mix in egg yolks.
Add water.
Cook and stir to a full boil.
Cool 5 minutes.
Blend in butter and lemon juice.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend until smooth (about 30 seconds).
Serve immediately. Makes about 3 cups.

title: miniature peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugars, egg, peanut butter and vanilla until creamy; add flour, baking soda and salt.
Chill until dough works nice into 1-inch balls.
Place in midget muffin tins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven; push a peanut butter cup down into center.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before removing from tins.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until well blended. Squeeze spinach to remove water.
Add spinach to mixture.
Add onions to mixture; stir well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: syrup
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Use on pancakes or waffles.
Store in refrigerator.

title: party time pork chops
directions: Combine brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Brush each pork chop with sugar mixture.
Preheat grill; cook chops about 4 inches from heat source, basting occasionally with sugar mixture.
Cook until chops are done.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.
Combine bananas, oil, honey, eggs and vanilla; add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Mix together the chicken, cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter, salt, pepper, milk and onion.
Divide into fourths.
Put 1/4 on each rectangle of crescent; fold over and pinch all sides together and seal.
Brush with remaining butter; sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Good!

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onions until the meat is well browned; drain.
Add sauerkraut and 2 tablespoons breadcrumbs. Combine the cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic powder and pepper; stir into sauerkraut mixture.
Chill.

title: sausage pilau
directions: Brown sausage and onion; add tomatoes and water. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Add rice. Cover and cook on low for 2 hours.

title: garden fresh macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water (2 quarts water plus 1 tablespoon salt) until tender yet firm, about 8 minutes.
Rinse in cold water in colander to cool.
Drain well. Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water to cool.
Drain well.
Gently but thoroughly mix together macaroni, vegetables, cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves if desired.
Makes a large bowl.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake in melted margarine.
Add 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Melt caramels in 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Pour chocolate chips over cake, then pour melted caramels over chips.
Pour on remaining batter. Bake for 18 minutes longer.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas and corn; mix these with other vegetables in a covered plastic bowl.
In a small saucepan, combine the sugar, vinegar, black pepper, salt and vegetable oil.
Bring to a boil, pour over vegetables.
Cool overnight.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Melt the butter in a large skillet.
Saute the onion until tender but not brown.
Add the chopped tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat until the tomatoes are soft. Don't let them get mushy.
This will probably take about 10 minutes.
Pour the mixture into the bowl of a food processor and while the machine is running, gradually add the heavy cream. Continue processing until the mixture is smooth.
Best served slightly warm.
A sprinkling of grated cheese over the top adds a nice taste boost.

title: charlie's spicy guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocados with the juice of a whole lemon.
Mix in the pressed or baked garlic cloves, finely chopped white onion, diced tomato, green chopped chiles and the sour cream.
Add milk as needed for consistency.
Season to taste with cayenne, Tabasco and salt.
Serve with unsalted tortilla chips.

title: forgotten rolls
directions: Mix 4 cups flour with the other ingredients at high speed with mixer for 3 minutes.
Add remaining 4 cups flour, or less, by hand. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled.
Roll or shape rolls. Cover.
Let rise until doubled again.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Sprinkle peaches with lemon juice and sugar.
Let set one hour.
Drain peaches and measure 1 cup syrup and blend with cornstarch.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Add extract and cool.
Pour some over shell and then pour over peaches in ready baked shell.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pack mixture into a greased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can serve topped with tomato sauce.

title: potatoes on a grill
directions: Mix together potatoes, green peppers and onion.
Season with paprika, salt and pepper.
Put mixture on heavy-duty foil and dab butter on top in several places.
(Spraying the inside of foil with Pam helps a lot!)
Wrap the potatoes in the foil real well and cook on grill, turning often, about 1/2 hour.
Can be done in oven at about 400°.

title: syro cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together;
then
add biscuit mix and dates and pecans.
Bake in oven at
350°	for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased pan.

title: pinehurst muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, pecans, apples, raisins and coconut.
In a bowl, beat 6 eggs, then add 2 cups Mazola oil and 4 teaspoons vanilla.
Stir in flour/fruit mixture until combined.
Spoon batter in well oiled muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until muffin springs back when touched.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Yields 36 regular sized muffins.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder in bowl.
Add milk and egg; beat until smooth.
Place 1-inch of oil in frying pan and heat.
Pour though funnel to make lines in oil.

title: moist and fruity rainbow cake
directions: Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean layer pans.
Prick each cake with serving fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and pour carefully over cakes.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip 1 cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds.
Turn out onto serving plate.
Top is 1 cup whipped topping or frosting.
Unmold second cake layer.
Place carefully on first layer.
Frost top and side with remaining whipped topping or frosting.
Garnish as directed.

title: mayonnaise bread
directions: Combine flour, milk and mayonnaise, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Grease a 10-inch cast-iron skillet with oil.
Place in a 400° oven for 4 minutes, or until hot. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon batter into skillet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese and green chilies mini quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease with margarine or butter a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Place chilies on bottom of pan.
Layer one cheese, then layer other cheese.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and tabasco sauce.
Pour over cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Freezes well.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Mix yeast and lukewarm water; set aside.
Put shortening, sugar and salt into bowl.
Add hot milk.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Beat egg and add it to yeast mixture, stir.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, stir; add 1 cup flour, stir.
Add 1 more cup flour and stir.
Grease hands; pinch off dough a little larger than an egg, work until rounded.
Put in baking pan, grease tops and let rise until double in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: In the bowl of an electric mixer, place butter and sugar.
Mix on low speed for 15 seconds.
Add flour and salt; continue mixing on low speed for 3 to 5 minutes, until the dough comes together. It will look dry just before it comes together.
Place the dough on a lightly floured board; roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out dough with a 3-inch star cutter or other desired shape.
Place on cookie sheets 1/2-inch apart.
Chill for 1 hour in the refrigerator or 1/2 hour in the freezer.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions.
Add broccoli for last 4 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat butter.
Add chicken and cook until browned, stirring often.
Add soup, milk, cheese, pepper and fettuccine mixture and cook through, stirring often.
Serves 4.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 10-inch springform pan.
Combine crumbs, almond extract and butter.
Press onto bottom of pan; refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, flour, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Beat in the eggs and egg yolks one at a time, until light and fluffy.
Beat in heavy cream, then amaretto.
Pour into prepared pan.
Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature.
Put in oven and bake 10 minutes; reduce the temperature to 250°, BUT DO NOT OPEN OVEN DOOR.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes more.
Remove from oven.
Immediately run a spatula around edge of cake to loosen from pan (helps prevent cracking).
Cool on wire rack for 1 hour, then cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Remove cheesecake from pan to serving container.
Top cheesecake with non-dairy whipped topping.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak red beans overnight; drain.
Add water and ham hocks; simmer several hours.
Add tomato ingredients, spices and sauteed ingredients.
Simmer all day.
Cook rice separately.
Serve with red beans.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute in margarine the onions and celery.
Combine soups and Cheez Whiz.
Next, combine all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 10 or 15 minutes at 375°.

title: fudgies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
(Start timing after the mixture reaches a full rolling boil.)
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered wax paper.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, shortening, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Fold in blueberries.
Makes one 8 x 8-inch square cake.
You may double recipe for a tube cake or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle batter with sugar before baking.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cut cooked chicken into chunks.

title: mocha macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease cookie sheet lightly.
Beat egg whites, coffee, cream of tartar and salt in medium bowl on High speed until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, on high speed.
Continue beating until stiff.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in cocoa and coconut.

title: quick marinated chicken
directions: Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Combine the dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Mix until well blended.
Layer half the sauce on the bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Place the chicken side-by-side on top.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: beer chicken
directions: Rinse chicken pieces with cool water.
Pat dry with paper towels.
In a large skillet, heat the oil.
Brown chicken pieces on all sides.
Sprinkle chopped onion, celery, garlic, salt and pepper over chicken.
Add enough beer to barely cover chicken. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is done to your liking.
Juices should run clear when pierced with a fork.
Serve hot with extra celery sprinkled over the top.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the 2 cheeses.
Roll into patties.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place a piece of Mozzarella cheese on each burger and sprinkle the Parmesan cheese on each slice of Mozzarella.
I use a cookie sheet for baking burgers.
Makes 4 burgers.

title: preparation of fresh wall-eye
directions: Soak fresh wall-eye in bowl of milk for 1 to 2 hours.
In skillet or pan melt butter.
Remove wall-eye from milk and roll in Progresso bread crumbs.
Cook until tender and brown to taste.
If baking fish, bake at 375° to 400° for 15 to 25 minutes or to desired taste.
Fish should be tender and flaky.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Simmer water, soy sauce and honey for 10 minutes.
Place chicken wings on a cookie sheet and baste with sauce.
Bake in a 275° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, turning and basting often.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain; rinse in cold water.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Add cold water, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Freeze in gallon milk jug or other
large
container.
Remove
from
freezer
about 4 hours before
serving
and
mix
with
ginger ale.
Only let it thaw partially.
Break it up with a fork and serve as an icy slush. It is wonderful!

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into patties.
Fry in pan with oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Batter will keep 1 week in refrigerator.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: sweet-sour macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni; when done, drain.
Mix in jar the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, Accent, garlic salt and mustard.
Mix well and chill.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in applesauce.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to applesauce mixture and stir in raisins and nuts.
Dip a good teaspoonful on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together. Put in pan. Bake 50 minutes at 350°. Serve warm topped with sweetened condensed milk poured over the top or with ice cream.

title: chicken with white wine
directions: Wash and pat dry the chicken breasts, skin on; salt and pepper.
Broil the chicken in a shallow pan or rimmed baking sheet about 4 to 5 inches from the heat for approximately 5 to 7 minutes per side or until well browned.
Remove the chicken from the broiler and set aside.

title: tomato salad
directions: Chop tomatoes in small pieces.
Add chopped green onions, sliced olives and crumbled Feta cheese and basil.
Mix well.
Add dressing to taste and toss.

title: cookie clusters
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients over low heat, cool slightly.	Add rice krispies and Spanish peanuts, then fold in marshmallows. Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.
Can put in refrigerator so the chocolate sets quicker.

title: adobo(popular filipino dish)
directions: *Can be prepared with pork or beef also.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows and mix.
Spread coconut on wax paper.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture on it into a log.
Roll in coconut and roll up and chill 24 hours.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices and serve.

title: steak casserole
directions: Cut steak in very small pieces and brown.
Mix with other ingredients and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Add to eggs the sugar, pumpkin and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Put in greased and floured cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in heavy Dutch oven (5-quart size). Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 9 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: easy casserole
directions: Fry sausage, hamburger, onion, celery and green pepper until done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in 2 layers.
Cool.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Crumble one cake layer into a large glass serving dish.
Pour 1/4 cup Kahlua over cake.
Top with half of the pudding, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and 1/2 of the crumbled Heath bars.
Repeat layers.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add cream cheese and beat until light and fluffy. Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: german tea cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll in small balls and flatten. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Place cookies on sheet covered with sifted powdered sugar as soon as taken from oven.
Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: chuck roast
directions: Place roast in heavy foil in roasting pan with A.1. sauce and sprinkle onion soup mix.
Then pour mushroom soup over chuck roast.
Wrap loosely in foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add lightly egg yolks.
Blend in mashed potatoes; combine cocoa with flour and cinnamon.
Add alternately with milk in which soda has been dissolved.
Then add enough flour to make normally thick cake batter.
Add nuts and fold in egg whites beaten stiff.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until a toothpick stuck in center comes out.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Combine in casserole dish green beans, soup concentrate, and 1/2 can of Durkee onions.
Mix together and spread evenly in casserole dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil.
Cover casserole with remaining 3 ounces of fried onions and bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool for 15 minutes.
Serve.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Mix
cheese and margarine (both room temperature).
Add remaining
ingredients.
Form
into
balls	and flatten with a fork on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chili beef potato topper
directions: In 1-quart microwave-safe casserole, crumble ground beef. Cover; microwave on High 3 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in soup, water and chili sauce. Cover; microwave 4 minutes.
Spoon over split baked potatoes. Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: mom's scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar; cream well.
Put the flour and cornstarch together, then sift again 2 times to be sure the two are well mixed.
Add a bit at a time to butter and sugar, mixing well.
(May have to knead with hands.)
On a dough board, pat the dough to a square about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into strips, 2 inches wide and length.
In a 300° oven, transfer strips to cookie sheet; bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Fingers will harden as they cool.
Do not store near heat.

title: homemade heath bars
directions: Bring brown sugar, margarine and butter to a boil over low heat.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Cover with a single layer of saltine crackers, laying side by side. Pour sugar and butter mixture over saltines.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with milk chocolate chips.
Spread until covered smoothly.
Refrigerate until cool.
Break up into bite size pieces.
Keep refrigerated, but sit out 1 hour before serving.

title: spinach balls
directions: Blend well.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine soft cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and mix well.
Spread on bottom of shell. Combine remaining ingredients.
Carefully pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve whipped cream on top, if desired.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in medium size pot; cook and stir onion, celery, green pepper and garlic over medium heat until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, parsley flakes, salt, cayenne red pepper and bay leaf.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cleaned shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until shrimp are done, about 10 minutes.
Serve on rice.

title: deviled ham roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent rolls onto waxed paper. Pat out to form triangle.

title: swedish gingerbread cookies
directions: Combine spices and baking soda. Add salt. Stir in butter.
Add molasses and sugar.
Mix well. Stir in egg and water.
Place flour in a large bowl. Make a well in the center.
Pour in mixture, gradually stirring in flour until completely incorporated.
Knead dough lightly in bowl until smooth ball forms. Shape dough into a disk. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for at least 8 hours.

title: creamed turnips
directions: Peel turnips and cook in salted water until tender; drain. Add lump of butter or margarine, flour, salt and black pepper. Then add a little milk or cream and cook until liquid thickens. Serve hot.
(Sugar may be added for sweetness.)

title: baked "fried" chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine melted butter or margarine, flour and mustard; mix until smooth.
In another medium bowl, combine cornflake crumbs, cornmeal and salt; mix well.
Dip each chicken wing in butter mixture, then roll in crumb mixture to coat.
Place chicken wings on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant halves
directions: Boil eggplant until soft, about 15 minutes.
Scoop out eggplant meat and dice.
Saute bell pepper, celery, onion and garlic until limp.
Add eggplant meat and smother on medium heat until most of the water is cooked out.
Add crawfish and cook 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and put in a bowl.
Fold in crabmeat and parsley.
Let cook for a little while and add enough bread crumbs to be firm enough to stuff eggplant.
Sprinkle bread crumbs, paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Blend egg, applesauce and oil together in a bowl and add to flour mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat stuffing for pepper or tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon bits slowly until golden brown.
Add onion and celery; cook on low heat until tender.
Add bread and seasonings. Combine crabmeat and beaten eggs; add to first mixture, stirring to blend.
Use this stuffing for baked stuffed peppers or tomatoes or acorn squash.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, flour, sugar, spices and salt.
Add egg yolks. Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: gaugenetti(an italian pastry usually prepared at christmas)
directions: Blend mixture well.
Food processor blender may be used.
Set aside and prepare pastry.

title: eggnog
directions: Put egg, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Mix with wire whisk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until egg mixture coats whisk.
Don't boil or mixture will curdle.
Pour in a glass bowl.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, stir with whisk.
Sprinkle on nutmeg.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk.
Gradually add beaten egg yolks.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add butter and flavoring; pour into baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 6 tablespoons of sugar and spread over pie filling. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Spray a 9 by 13 pan with vegetable oil.
Combine ingredients in a lrg. bowl, blend with electric mixer on low for 1 min. Scrape bowl and mix on med. for 2 min.
Pour batter into pan and bake until it springs back when touched with your finger.
Remove from oven and place on a wire rack.
Immediately punch holes in the top with a drinking straw or chopstick.

title: mama's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sugar, spices and salt, stir in sweet potatoes.
Combine eggs, milk and butter.
Add to sweet potato mixture.
Turn into pastry shell and bake in 400° oven about 40 minutes, or until filling is set.
Yields one 9-inch pie.
Top and serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut balls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour margarine over and form into balls. Dip in chocolate melted with wax in double boiler.

title: ham casserole
directions: Melt
cup margarine; stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring
constantly until thickened.
Add cheese; cook slowly until
melted.
Add
almonds.
Arrange
potatoes
in greased
2 1/2-quart casserole; cover with green beans.
Pour half the cheese sauce over green beans; add ham and remaining sauce.
Melt remaining
margarine;
mix
with
bread
crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake
for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Blend sugar and flour.
Then in a saucepan, bring to boil the next 3 ingredients.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture then mix and add buttermilk, soda, and eggs, then add vanilla. Put in 11 x 16 inch pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins and onion.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour this over broccoli.
Before serving, add bacon (can also add nuts or sesame seed).

title: copper pennies
directions: Use mayonnaise instead of butter.
It's good!

title: bow tie casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Divide into two (9 x 13-inch) pans. Brown the ground chuck and drain.
Cut pepperoni into half moon shapes, add to sauce and simmer.
Grate the Provolone cheese and add to sauce.
Stir the browned chuck into sauce and pour over the noodles.
Top with slices of Mozzarella cheese (8 slices per pan). Bake at 350° until the cheese is melted.
Halve the recipe for 1 pan.

title: toffee chocolate chip nut cookies
directions: Beat butter; add sugars and vanilla until creamy. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each. Add flour, baking soda and salt and beat on low. Add chips and nuts, mixing by hand. Drop by rounded tablespoons on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 9 to 11 minutes at 350°.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl, then store in an airtight container in a cool dry place.
Can be kept for up to 3 months. To prepare hot cocoa, dissolve 1/3 c. mix in boiling water.
Top each cup with miniature marshmallows if desired.
Makes about 21 cups of hot cocoa.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayo, sugar and vinegar. Stir into remaining ingredients until coated. Chill.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Add salt, oil and sugar to milk and heat to 120° to 130°. Pour mixture over yeast.
Add flour and mix well.
Scrape dough onto a heavily floured surface (dough will be sticky).
Liberally sprinkle top of dough with more flour.
Roll out; cut out rounds with biscuit cutter.
Fold over and allow to rise on cookie sheet for 1 hour in a warm place.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. After removing from oven, rub butter over tops and cover with a towel.
Serves 15.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter and cocoa.
Heat in pan until mixture slow-boils for 30 seconds.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and coconut.
After thoroughly mixing, put tablespoon-size balls on wax paper and let cool.

title: butter (cutout) cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy. Add unbeaten egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll on well-floured board; cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 400° for 6 minutes.

title: fine cup fruit saladfort collins, colorado
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Will keep well, so can be made ahead.

title: filled meat balls
directions: Mix first three ingredients together well.
Make filling with remaining ingredients.
Roll out meat mixture on floured board. Place wax paper on top of meat mixture before rolling.
Cut rolled out meat in six squares.
Put filling ball in center or meat, pull meat up around filling and seal all edges.
Brown in Crisco, turning all around.
Remove balls and make gravy (can use some beef bouillon for more flavor).
Cover and simmer balls in gravy for 1 hour on low heat.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients. Blend in egg and onion. With hands, mold mixture into little cakes, about 1 tablespoon each.
Fry in about 1-inch deep fat until well browned. Drain on paper.
Serve hot.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Combine sauce and ginger.
Add beef; toss and set aside.
Leave an hour or more.
Prepare vegetables.
Heat oil in frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
If not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables. Toss until vegetables are tender and crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan.
Stir and cook until thick. Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: blaukraut(german; rotkraut - red cabbage)
directions: Remove cabbage core.
Put shredded cabbage, apples, bay leaf, salt and cloves into bowl.	Pour vinegar over it and mix well. Cover
and	let
sit
overnight.
The
next
day,
heat shortening in a large pot.
Add the cabbage mixture, the water and sugar. Cook until tender.	Season with salt and pepper.

title: honey baked georgia sweet onions
directions: Peel and trim onions.
Cut in half and place in a buttered, oblong baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over onions.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in unbaked pie crust. Sprinkle with a little cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast all in one
directions: Mix ingredients with fork or whisk.
Brown sausage, drain and cool.
Mix eggs and milk; add seasonings.
Mix well.
Mix in the bread to egg mixture to soften.
Add sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Prepare night before cooking and refrigerate.

title: percolator punch
directions: Grate rind from lemon, lime and 1 orange.
Place rind in basket of percolator.
Squeeze juice from fruit into percolator. Slice remaining orange.
Pour Hawaiian punch into percolator with fruit juices.
Insert basket and stem.
Pour honey over fruit rind.
Bring to a boil and perk for 10 minutes.
Pour punch into mugs and garnish with orange slices.
Serves about 9.

title: ilene's dream barsspringfield, missouri
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt sifted with nutmeats.
Mix thoroughly and spread. Bake 20 minutes in oven and cool slightly before cutting into bars.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions into slices; separate into rings.
Place rings in Pyrex casserole.
Mix soup and milk; spoon over onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until top is golden brown and bubbly.
Excellent with beef.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: In a trifle bowl or glass salad bowl, place 1 cake layer on bottom.
Spoon 1/2 of chocolate pudding on cake layer.
Sprinkle 3 crushed Skor bars on pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over Skor bars. Repeat layers.
Grate Hershey's Kisses over Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sirloin beef tips
directions: Brown beef cubes in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer on low heat 2 hours or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: spaghetti cheese bake
directions: Brown chuck in large pan and drain.
Add tomato sauce, spaghetti mix and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring often for 30 minutes.
Break spaghetti and cook according to package directions.
Drain and keep warm.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Add evaporated milk and water, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Add 3/4 cup of shredded cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Using two 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dishes, layer spaghetti, tomato sauce and cheese sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Add nuts and strawberries and freeze.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Boil sugar and water until threads.
Add salted pecans. Remove from fire and stir until pecans are crystallized. Separated the pecans.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch square pan, layer broccoli, chicken breasts and Swiss cheese slice over each breast.
Spread soup evenly over top. Add half a can of water in sides of pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for at least 1 hour (1 1/2 if everything was still very frozen). Check.
When bubbly and brown on top, it's done.
You can leave it for two, whatever, but check and add water if it starts to dry. Serve with rice.
Rolls are nice.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
Cream together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in Baby Ruth candy bars and dry ingredients until well blended.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Drop dough by 1/2 teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Remove from sheet and cool on wire rack.

title: lemon cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, add ingredients as given, one at a time, until you have used everything, then beat with an electric beater until well mixed.
Pour in a well-greased Bundt pan and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate delite
directions: Mix thoroughly flour, salt, nuts and butter.
Press in pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool.
Beat well cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Add cold milk to puddings and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: never-fail chess pie
directions: Mix sugar with flour and meal.
Add butter and cream.
Beat yolks; add milk and vanilla and mix well.
Bake in uncooked pastry shell for 45 minutes in hot oven (375°).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Mix flour, oats. soda and powder together.
Add to creamed ingredients. Mix on low speed just until blended.
Add chocolate chips and candy bar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: spicy apple cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Add eggs.
Stir in apples, nuts, raisins and chips.
Add dry ingredients with juice. Bake on greased sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from sheet while warm.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla, blending well.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup will be hot.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture into nonstick coated cookie sheet.
Spread as thin as desired.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour. Break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: grandmother's gone to heaven dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans well and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.*

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onion and chilies.
Combine eggs, corn and milk.
Add cornbread mix.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist; mixture will be thin.
Pour 1/2 of corn mixture into greased 9 x 9-inch dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Top with cheese. Cover with remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Great served with red beans.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Process in blender until smooth.

title: jelly muffins
directions: Cream together the brown sugar, shortening, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Add 1/2 teaspoon raspberry jam.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: kosher dills
directions: Soak cucumbers overnight in cold water.
Next day, fill jars with cucumbers (may be whole, sliced or spears).
Into each quart jar, put 1 head or 3 tablespoons dill, 1/4 teaspoon alum and 1 small clove garlic.
Bring the water, white vinegar and canning salt to a rolling boil.
Cover the cucumbers with the boiling brine.
Seal; turn upside down.
(If they do not seal, redo brine process or refrigerate.)
Jars will not crack if they are sterilized before being packed, so are hot.
Pickles should stay crisp.

title: cindy reagon's squash casserole
directions: Put squash in bowl and mash to a pulp.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Grease Dutch oven with butter. Alternate crackers, squash and cheese until half full.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple well.
Sprinkle Jell-O over Cool Whip and mix.
Fold in fruit and cottage cheese.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serves 20.

title: busy day salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pudding in water until dissolved.
Set aside to thicken.
Add pineapple and juice and rest of ingredients, except Cool Whip.
When mixed, fold in Cool Whip.

title: cottage cheese mold
directions: Mix the jellos with the boiling water and cool.
Combine the rest of the ingredients with the cooled jello.
Pour into a mold and chill.

title: marinated spiced carrots
directions: Cook carrots (not too soft).
Combine remaining ingredients except onion and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion and pepper and bring to a boil again.
Pour over carrots and let stand. After cooling, refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.

title: black forest cake
directions: Top with half of Cool Whip, then half of pie filling.
Top this with second layer. Finally put on top remaining Cool Whip, then remaining pie filling.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Put oil and garlic in saucepan or low pot.
Saute garlic until it starts
to
turn
gold.
Immediately pour in tomatoes. Add basil and sugar.
Stir occasionally over medium flame for 1 hour or until desired flavor is reached (1 1/2 hours).

title: chilled broccoli salad
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix together broccoli, bacon, raisins and onion.
Pour dressing over salad.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Serve cold.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Slice muffins in half, then halve again, making 4 pieces. Arrange on cookie sheet.
Squeeze crab meat dry.
Mix with other ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Broil until bubbly.
Serve hot.
Can be frozen.

title: best buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: corn chowder
directions: Preparation Time is 10 minutes; cooking time is 25 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes; prick several times with a fork and bake at 400° for 1 hour. Let cool. Cut in half and scoop out pulp. Melt butter over low heat; add flour and stir until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; stir until thick and bubbly. Add potatoes, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onion, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese. Cook until heated through. Stir in sour cream. Add extra milk if necessary for desired thickness. Serve with remaining onion, bacon and cheese. Serves 10 cups.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in a jelly roll size pan, or a cookie sheet with 1-inch sides.
Cook flour and milk until thick.
Let cool.
Combine sugar, Crisco and 1 stick of butter.
Cream well with mixer.
Add to cooled mixture.
Mix until creamy.
Spread on slightly warm cake.
Mix other stick of butter with remaining ingredients.
Spread on cooled cake and add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: eggplant pie
directions: Peel eggplant, cut into cubes.
Dice onion and celery.
Cook until tender, drain and mash.
Add other ingredients to mixture and mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased glass pie plate or shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mr. goodbars
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips together.
Blend in peanut butter.
Fold in peanuts and marshmallows.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate. Cut at room temperature.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until Jell-O is well dissolved and mixed.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix all with spoon, except cramberries.
Add cranberries.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place drained pineapple in greased casserole.
Mix together cheese, sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Mix together the crushed crackers and melted margarine; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: green vegetable salad
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, oil, pepper and salt until sugar dissolves.
Then pour over vegetables.
Let set.
Keeps well.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Return cut-up chicken to broth.
Add bouillon cubes, 1 to 2 cans of cream of chicken soup and 2 packages of dry soup mix.
Dice onions and add.
Cook in crock-pot.
tags: cream of chicken dry soup mix

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil. Add broccoli and onion. Boil 10 to 12 minutes.
Add seasonings and cheese. Stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, cream and butter. Stir and heat to boiling. Slowly add water to flour until texture is smooth.
Slowly add to hot mixture, stirring rapidly. Reduce heat and stir until soup is consistency of heavy cream. Best if made a day ahead.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and beat. Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk and flour.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix soda and vinegar together.
Add to mixture.
Do not beat.
Just fold in gently.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) cake pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: best pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper meat; rub with flour.
In heavy cast-iron roasting pan, saute onion and garlic until translucent, not brown (15 minutes).
Brown meat on both sides after browning onion and garlic.
Add boiling water, carrots, beans, tomatoes, bay leaf, Kitchen Bouquet and salt and pepper if desired.
Cook covered. Cook 20 minutes (baste).
Continue cooking and basting every 15 minutes, turning meat over once.
You may need additional water. Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours until meat is falling apart tender.
Remove meat and vegetables.
Make gravy from drippings.

title: zucchini pickle
directions: Wash zucchini and cut in thin slices.
Peel and cut onions in quarters, then slice very thin.
Add zucchini and cover with 1-inch water; add salt.
Let stand 2 hours; drain thoroughly.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend pudding and milk until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and about 2/3 of Cool Whip.
Pour over layers of wafers and sliced bananas.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Let set about 30 minutes in refrigerator before serving.
(If you desire a thinner mixture, use 6 cups of milk.)

title: fruit-glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper; brush with melted butter.
Place in a shallow baking pan. Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Combine fruit concentrate and sherry; heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken and bake 1/2 hour longer, basting frequently.
When chicken is tender and glazed, remove to hot serving dish.
Blend cornstarch with cold water; stir into pan liquid.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Serve with hot buttered rice.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: caramel pie
directions: Take wrappers off of condensed milk cans and put cans in pot. Cover the cans with water and boil cans for 3 hours.
Make sure cans are continually covered with water.
After 3 hours, let cans cool.
Pour into ready pie crust.
Cover with whipped cream and top with chocolate chips.

title: baked hamburger steak
directions: Divide hamburger in half.
Quarter potato, put around hamburger.
Add a dash of A.1. sauce and soy sauce.
Place in onion on top of hamburger, sliced.
Wrap each in aluminum foil. Bake in oven 45 minutes at 400°.

title: congo squares
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine melted shortening and sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture and blend.
Stir in nuts and chocolate morsels.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When almost cool, cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 48 squares.

title: beef tips
directions: Cut steak in chunks and brown in shortening.
Put in baking dish; add juice from pan and water.
Add mushrooms and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hobo hamburgers
directions: Shape
hamburger into 4 patties and place each patty in a square
of	aluminum foil.	Place 1 potato and carrot around each patty.
Place
onion
slices on top of each patty.	Close and seal foil.
Place
on
baking sheet and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake in casserole for about 2 hours in 300° oven.

title: beef brisket
directions: Salt and pepper brisket.
Brown fat side of brisket in a large frying pan.
Put brisket in roasting pan, brown side up.
Brown onion in frying pan.
Place on top of brisket.
Place carrots and celery around brisket; add 1 cup of water.
Cover and cook 3 hours at 350°.
When done, remove from pan.
Stir in cornstarch and water to make gravy.

title: tv bolts and nuts
directions: Melt butter.
Add salt and garlic salt together.
Put other ingredients in turkey roaster and mix with hands thoroughly, then pour in melted butter and salts.
Mix thoroughly again.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Saute onion, garlic and parsley in margarine.
Add cheese and half and half, then add shrimp.
Simmer on medium to low heat for about 20 minutes, stir constantly.
Boil noodles.
Pour this mixture over noodles.
May reserve some of cheese to top.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soup and sour cream; add poppy seed.
Mix crushed cracker crumbs with margarine.
Layer in a casserole dish (13 x 8-inch) with sauce on bottom, chicken in middle and cracker crumbs on top. Do this twice.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Melt margarine and mix with sugar-egg mixture.
Add milk, vanilla flavoring and 1 cup coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put 1/2 cup coconut on top of mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix meal, flour, egg, soda and buttermilk in bowl.
Heat oil in cast-iron skillet or 8 to 9-inch cake pan until very hot.
Sprinkle in cornmeal and pour in bread dough. Place in oven and bake until brown on top.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine orange juice, peel, shortening and enough water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Stir in egg. Pour into dry ingredients.
Mix just enough to dampen.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Spread into pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch, higher around the outside edges.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Slices best the next day.

title: calico kitty cookies
directions: Cut 1/4-inch slices. Place cookie dough on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: sunshine salad(orange, pineapple and carrot)
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch container. Dissolve well before adding cold liquid.
Let set to consistency of egg whites, then add drained pineapple and carrots. Refrigerate until firm.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in a saucepan. Add boiling water and cook. Stir until clear and thickened.

Let stand until completely cold. With an electric beater at high speed, beat eggs until foamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff but not dry. Turn mixer to low and add salt and vanilla. Gradually beat in cold cornstarch mixture. Turn mixer again to high speed and beat well. Spread meringue on cool dessert. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
This meringue cuts beautifully and doesn't get sticky. You will love this!

title: light caramel icing
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients in saucepan; stir and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in powdered sugar to right consistency to spread on cake.
This is good for banana cake.

title: gene autry peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the peanut butter, cream cheese, sugar and melted butter.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Add fudge topping.
Pour into prepared crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fruited trifle
directions: Brush cake slices generously with pineapple juice.
Arrange half of the slices in single layer in trifle or other deep clear glass bowl.
Layer with half of strawberries, bananas, orange sections (or blueberries) and kiwi.
Spoon half of custard over fruit.
Repeat layering with remaining ingredients.
Whip cream in bowl until soft peaks form.
Add powdered sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Spoon cream over top of trifle and garnish with strawberries.	Chill until ready to serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, milk, 1/2 cup butter, vanilla and potatoes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, nuts, flour and 1/3 cup butter.
Place crumbles on top of potato mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This dish can be frozen before baking.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower covered for 3 minutes on High.
Turn and cook 3 minutes longer.
Mix Miracle Whip and mustard and cauliflower. Sprinkle cheese over cauliflower and heat in microwave until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: plain pastry
directions: Blend flour and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut fat into dry ingredients with pastry blender or fork.
Sprinkle water evenly over dry mixture, toss and blend until all portions are evenly dampened.
Press mixture into a ball.
Place ball of dough on lightly floured wax paper.
Pat dough ball flat and then roll from center outward with floured rolling pin.
Carefully lift rolled dough on the wax paper and turn over into 8-inch or 9-inch pie pan.
Be careful to not stretch pastry.
Prick bottom with fork. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put water and butter in pan.
Bring to a boil, then put flour in and stir until smooth.
Add eggs; stir until mixed well.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: steak marinade
directions: Heat mixture til onions are tender 'n then thicken wid 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Pore this tantalizin' mixture over cooked rice 'n serve wid the steak.
Oh, slice meat diagonally!

title: popovers
directions: Mix and
sift
flour
and salt.
Combine eggs, milk and shortening; gradually
add
to
flour mixture, beating about 1 minute or
until batter is smooth.
Fill greased, sizzling hot pans 3/4 full
and
bake
in
very
hot
oven
(450°) about 20 minutes; reduce heat
to 350° and continue baking for 15 or 20 minutes.
Very good served with chicken salad for lunch or any time.
Cut top
off
popover
and fill with salad or fill with pudding for dessert.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Brown sausage with onions, celery and bell pepper.
Drain. Crumble corn bread into large bowl, add stuffing mix.
Stir in sage and salt and pepper; add sausage mixture.
Mix well.
Add broth; mix well.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Save broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place chicken in greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing, onion and celery.
Stir in enough reserved broth to moisten.
Season stuffing with poultry seasoning, if desired.
Spoon over chicken and soup in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken paprikash(yields 4 servings)
directions: In large skillet, brown onions in 1 stick butter.
Add chicken, paprika and salt.
Brown on medium-low heat.
Add 1/2 cup chicken stock.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles as directed on package and add frozen peas to cooking noodles.
Remove from heat.
Stir sour cream into chicken mixture, then add noodles and peas mixture and serve.
Garnish with parsley.
Enjoy!

title: mary's dill pickles
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 5 minutes.
In washed, scalded jars place 2 cloves garlic and 1 large head dill.
Fill with sliced cucumbers.
Cover with boiling vinegar mix.
Process as desired.

title: meat and cheese loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Mix well.
Press into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: large cheese ball
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor except 1 package of corned beef; mix well and form into a ball.
Makes 1 large or 2 regular size.
Process remaining package of corned beef into shreds.
Put on waxed paper and roll your cheese ball over it to coat the outsides.
Chill until needed.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: anise cookies
directions: Mix; knead into soft dough enough to handle and roll out.
Cut in 2-inch strips about 10-inches long.
Place on greased cookie sheet and twist into a bow.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until golden brown.
Frost with sugar, milk and vanilla glaze.

title: jeanne's breakfast brunch dish
directions: Prepare 5 slices of bread in a 9 x 10-inch buttered dish. Sprinkle in cheese and ham.
Mix eggs, milk, 1/4 cup butter, salt and mustard.
Pour over ham and cheese; sprinkle rest of bread cubes.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Pour boiling water over rhubarb and let stand 5 minutes. Drain; add sugar and flour and mix well.
Add egg yolks beaten with the water and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in moderate oven; cover with meringue made with egg whites and brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs.
Beat bananas and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla to chocolate mix.
Add chocolate mixture to batter.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add with buttermilk to chocolate batter, beating well until smooth.
Beat egg whites until peak forms.
Fold into batter.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch pans, well-greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, margarine, flour and salt.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook over rapidly boiling water 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix small amount of mixture with egg yolks.
Return to double boiler and cook 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup coconut and vanilla.
Cool.
Turn into pie shell.
Whip egg whites until stiff, adding sugar.
Spread over coconut mixture.
Cook 15 minutes or until brown.

title: party chicken
directions: Roll each chicken breast half in a piece of bacon.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with chipped beef that has been rinsed in water.
Arrange chicken halves on top.
Combine soups and sour cream and mix well.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for three hours.
Serve over rice, spooning sauce over.

title: rhubarb honey pudding
directions: Blend shortening, 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons honey, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in bread cubes and corn flakes. Spread rhubarb in 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish; top with remaining 3/4 cup honey.
Cover with corn flake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until rhubarb is done.

title: mrs. n. r. williams' avocado fruit salad
directions: Cut avocado in small cubes.
Cut apple fine.
Slice bananas and add celery.
Mix together with mayonnaise made with lemon juice.

title: veal cordon bleu with mushroom sauce(serves 4)
directions: Lay 2 slices of ham on each of 4 veal cutlets.
Sprinkle generously with Romano and Parmesan cheese.
Top with remaining veal and press edges together tightly to seal.
Dredge lightly in flour.
Dip into egg, then roll in seasoned breadcrumbs.
Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add veal and saute until golden, turning once.
Remove from pan and keep warm. Add shallot, green pepper and garlic to skillet and saute until almost tender.
Stir in mushrooms and pepper.
Reduce heat, return veal to skillet and simmer about 2 minutes to heat through, turning once.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Dip chicken in melted margarine.
Coat with combined dry ingredients (cheese, bread crumbs and spices).
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Coat chicken with flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time and brown on all sides.
Remove as browned to shallow roasting pan, arranging pieces, skin side up. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: green chili dip
directions: In a food processor, combine the cilantro, scallions, jalapenos and salt and process, stopping once to scrape down the sides of the work bowl, until smooth.
In a bowl, whisk the sour cream until smooth and shiny.
Stir in the puree and combine well. Taste; correct the seasoning and refrigerate, covered, until serving time.

title: fat-free 3 bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Ice cookies when cool.

title: pineapple pie(almost sugarless)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in crust. Refrigerate.
May be frozen.
Suggest cut into pieces before freezing.

title: full o'boloney
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate.)
Arrange potatoes, bologna, green pepper, flour and seasonings in layers in 1 1/2-quart baking dish, dotting each layer with butter.
Pour milk over and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, dice and boil eggplant; drain.
Crush crackers; add chopped onion, eggs, cheeses, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken creamette casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves 10.

title: sour cream spinach
directions: Cook spinach and onion in small amount of water until thawed. Drain.
Beat eggs slightly and mix with other ingredients.
Stir spinach and onion into mixture.
Bake in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Do not overcook as casserole will separate.

title: layered taco salad dip
directions: For the first layer, mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
The second layer is salsa, third layer is lettuce and fourth layer is grated cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: black eyed pea salad
directions: Bring vinegar, oil and sugar to a boil. Pour mixture over veggies. Stir cook and refrigerate.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Split and toast the muffins.
Spread 1/2 tablespoon of pizza sauce on each muffin.
Layer the pepperoni and the cheese on the muffins.
Bake muffins for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix together 3 cups flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt.
In mixer bowl, beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and oil; beat until well mixed.
Add vanilla and half the dry ingredients.
Add remaining dry ingredients and zucchini, mixing by hand.

title: lemon lush(makes 3 layers)
directions: Blend together.
Press with fingers into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 hour (very, very cool).

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and Dream Whip until smooth.
Layer cream cheese mix with bluebeery into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Cut cheese into twenty 1/2-inch cubes.
Shred remaining cheese; set aside.
Mix next 7 ingredients.
Shape each portion around cheese cube.
Brown in oil.
Add spaghetti sauce to pan.
Simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Great in a crock-pot.

title: cheese torte
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and sugar thoroughly and press evenly into 9-inch round pan.
Sift sugar, flour and salt.
Cut cream cheese into sifted ingredients and add 1/2 cup milk, egg yolks and vanilla and mix well.
Fold in 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Bring cream cheese and Cool Whip to room temperature.
Blend in mixing bowl.
Add strawberries and some of the juice.
Add sliced bananas.
Add pineapple (drained) and pecans, if desired.
Mix well.
Fold into loaf pans.
Recipe makes 2 pans.
Freeze for at least 8 hours before serving.
Can remain in freezer 6 to 8 weeks.

title: spinach provencial
directions: Wash the spinach carefully or defrost thoroughly.
In large kettle, heat olive oil and saute onion and garlic for a few minutes until onion is transparent.
Add spinach.
Cover tightly for 2 to 3 minutes, then stir into onion.
Grease medium sized baking dish with butter.
When spinach has cooled slightly, stir in 2 beaten eggs and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Season with salt and pepper and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese over the top and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
We serve this with rice on the side.

title: lamb shanks - oven roast
directions: Cut a slit in each shank and insert clove of garlic.
Roll shanks in flour, salt and paprika and brown in oil.
Remove shanks to large baking pan.
Add lemon juice to frying pan and mix with brown bits and gravy.
Add bay leaves and peppercorns.
Pour this over shanks.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add quartered sweet potatoes, green beans and salt.
Cover and bake until meat is well cooked.
Allow one shank per person.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar; pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix gelatin and warm water; set aside.
Cook the rest of ingredients on stove until thick.
Add gelatin mixture.
Beat egg whites and add pumpkin mixture to egg whites.
Let set and top with whipped cream.

title: home happiness cake(from my mother's cookbook)
directions: Add 2 large portions of sense of humor beaten separately, spice to taste with fun and nonsense.
Bake in moderate oven of warm approval.
Ice with generous appreciation.

title: sugar-free lemon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup of hot water.
Combine slightly beaten eggs, 1 3/4 cups water, salt, lemon peel and lemon juice in top of double boiler.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water.
When mixture begins to cook, add gelatin mixture and cornstarch mixture.
Cook until mixture coats spoon, stirring often.
Cool. When cool but not congealed, add Equal.
Set in refrigerator. When mixture starts to set, pour into baked pie shell.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix drained hominy, soup, milk, chilies, cheese and onions. Pour in casserole dish. Top with crumbled crackers and butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples and water in a saucepan; cover with lid and cook 5 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, alternately, with dry ingredients.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Cook onion in bacon grease; drain.
Mix all ingredients in heavy pan or crock-pot.
Cook on low temperature for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken biscuits
directions: Roll the dough to a round sheet 1/4-inch thick. Cover with chopped chicken. Roll as a jelly roll and slice into pieces 1-inch thick. Place on greased sheet. Bake for 15 minutes at 425°. Serve with chicken broth, thickened to make gravy.

title: easy shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: turkey burgers
directions: In a bowl, mix the ground turkey with bread crumbs, parsley, egg, salt and pepper.
