Cover and refrigerate.
Heat oil in skillet; add onion.
Cook over high heat until brown; stir in garlic and remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature, then stir into turkey mixture.
In an oiled skillet or grill, cook turkey patties about 5 minutes on each side.
Serve on a bun with lettuce and tomato.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add soup, milk and Ro-Tel tomatoes to meat.
Heat over medium heat.
Stir and simmer 5 minutes.
Add sliced cheese to mixture and simmer over low heat until cheese is melted. Serve warm with chips or crackers.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients and sauce (recipe to follow).
Place in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: bean soup
directions: Mix in large cooker.
Let cook a few minutes.
Serve with hot cornbread.
Very good on a cold winter night.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare Jiffy corn bread mix according to package directions. Crumble corn bread in casserole dish.
Chop onion, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Sprinkle these over crumbled corn bread.
Then add salad pickles and pour juice over all ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise on top of all.
Top with grated cheese and bacon bits to taste.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, garlic and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bar cheese
directions: In a double boiler, stir ingredients until thoroughly heated. Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into containers.
Keeps 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: honey bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix cereal and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg, honey and butter.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and raisins.
Sprinkle over bran mixture.
Stir just until blended. Fill greased pans 2/3 full.
Sprinkle top with wheat germ, if you desire.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 12 regular size muffins.

title: pork chops and onion rice
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of oil.
Pat rice in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Arrange drained pork chops on top of rice. Add water.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven until water is absorbed by the rice (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: irmik tatlisi(farina dessert)
directions: Pour milk, farina and sugar in a medium pan.
Boil at medium heat.
Put half of the mixture into small cups.
Put grated apples and walnuts onto it.
Put the remaining mixture.
Wait until the mixture thickens.
Dress the dessert with cinnamon and coconut.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together (except cornflakes) and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix well, pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.
Add cubed ham or chicken.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; add 2 tablespoons sugar and mix all to a soft dough with beaten egg and milk.
Beat well.
Turn into a greased pan.
Spread evenly.
Brush over with melted butter; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion in hot butter or oil.
Combine kidney beans and tomato soup.
Mix together chili powder, flour, water and salt to make a paste and blend into soup mixture.
Add to ground beef and cook 45 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: tomburgers
directions: Combine barbecue sauce (the one that simmers real cookout flavor all through the meat) with turkey, green pepper and onion. Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Cover top halves of 6 hamburger buns with slices of cheese spread.
Broil until cheese melts. Spoon turkey mixture on bottom halves.

title: cheese squares
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1 package crescent rolls on bottom of pan, patting serration together.
Beat together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread over rolls.
Place second package of rolls on top of cheese mixture, pinching serration together.
Beat egg white with a fork and spread over top layer of crescent rolls.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and almonds.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve warm or cold.

title: shells with spinach and ricotta
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray an 8-inch square pan.
Heat oil in skillet; saute onions and garlic.
Add spinach, chicken broth and pepper; mix.
Add Ricotta and milk; stir.
Add nutmeg and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Add shells.
Put in the 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: mexican bread(pan casero)
directions: Beat together sifted sugar, baking powder and melted butter. Add eggs.
Slowly add the flour, the orange juice, cinnamon and milk until mixture is thick but somewhat runny.
Pour into loaf pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lentil soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add all ingredients in crock pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
Note:
You may cook in large kettle on low heat for 2 hours.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix in order given.
Heat griddle until a drop of water dances.
Drop batter by spoonfuls and cook until bubbles form; turn brown on topside.
Done when steaming stops.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Place half of crumbled cornbread in the bottom of a large bowl.
Top with half of the tomatoes, peppers, onion, corn, cheese and bacon.
Pour on some of the salad dressing.
Repeat all layers again and top with dressing.
Cover and chill for 2 or 3 hours.
If you can't find Tex Mex mix, add one 4 ounce can chopped chili to your favorite cornbread mix.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ham and cheese and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields about 4 to 6 servings.

title: poached fish
directions: In a large shallow pan, saute the onion and celery in oil until tender.
Place skinned fillets on top of vegetables, or roll each fillet; secure with a toothpick and place on vegetables.
Add water or wine and seasonings.
Cover and simmer about 8 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Carefully transfer fillets to a heated platter.
Serve with lemon parsley sauce. Approximate calories/serving:

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice, margarine and onion soup mix into baking dish. Arrange chicken pieces on top of rice.
Cover with water.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 375°.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes of baking to allow chicken to brown.

title: farmer's bread with ham, cheese and white sauce
directions: Arrange 8 slices of farmer's bread on cookie sheet.
Cover farmer's bread with 2 slices each of ham; top with 1/2 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Salt and pepper all 8 slices.
Close sandwiches.
Spoon white sauce over each sandwich.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Broil for 4 minutes in oven until bubbly. Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sherry beef
directions: Put raw meat into 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to beef.
Stir well.
Cover.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours in 325° oven.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Mix first five ingredients and heat well.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix hamburger and soup (do not add water to soup) and place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Cover all with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: no guilt chicken fettucini
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in two tablespoons of diet margarine. While this is cooking, mix together the soup, milk and cream cheese.
Add to the meat mixture.
Heat through and serve over noodles.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In blender combine water, sugar and Jell-O; blend.
Wash and drain cranberries, core apple and slice orange.
Add to blender and blend.
(Optional:
Add pecans to mixture.)
Pour mixture into mold and chill.

title: crisp frozen pea salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 12-inch dish: lettuce, celery, onion, water chestnuts and peas.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, followed by eggs and bacon.
Decorate with tomato wedges.
Fix the day before and refrigerate.
Can be refrigerated several days.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating them well.
Add lemon extract.
Add sifted dry ingredients and cream mixture.
Add fruits and nuts (flour lightly), using about 1/3 cup cake flour. Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or bake in tube pan 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon nutmeg scones
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, combine flour, cornstarch, baking soda and a 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg; blend well.
Using a pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
In small bowl, combine 1/2 of the lemon yogurt, raisins and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients all at once; stir just until moistened (dough will be sticky).

title: sour cream and potato casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika and parsley over all and bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bar over low heat; cool slightly.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill well.

title: chicken noodle barbecue
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Sprinkle with chili powder when pieces are turned.
Remove chicken.
Add onions and garlic; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken; cover and simmer.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: super apple pie
directions: In a skillet, combine apples, sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to simmer over medium heat.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, dissolve cornstarch in a 1/4 cup of water; stir into apple mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring occasionally for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, cinnamon and nutmeg. Put this in a pie shell and bake in oven at 350° until crust is golden.
Serve warm with scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread and eggs.
Form into balls.
In saucepan, bring tomato soup and water to a boil.
Add meatballs.
Cook 45 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine oil and unsweetened chocolate. Blend well with an electric mixer.
Add granulated sugar and continue to mix.
Add the eggs, one at a time, incorporating each egg into the mixture before adding the next.
Blend in the flour and baking powder.
Add the vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate the mixture for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Use a 13 x 9-inch or 2 large loaf pans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and flour.
Mix well.
Add pineapple with juice.
Stir until combined.
Fold in carrots.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: overnight egg casserole
directions: Place bread into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish and sprinkle with cheese; set aside.
In skillet brown sausage and drain fat. Crumble sausage over the cheese and bread.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, soup and water together and pour over sausage mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: greek easter bread
directions: Combine milk, salt, butter, orange rind and sugar.
Bring to boil and then cool.
Put warm water in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with yeast and dissolve.
Add milk mixture and beat in half of flour. Add remaining flour alternately with eggs.
Stir until dough leaves sides of bowl and is very stiff.
Knead until smooth and elastic (3 to 5 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl, cover and let raise until doubled.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn; leave in big pan.
Bring rest of ingredients to a boil over medium heat.
Heat and stir constantly for 2 minutes. Pour over popcorn, stirring constantly until popcorn is completely coated.
Dip hands in cold water and form into balls.
Eat!

title: mexican bean casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions, saute.
Mix in jalapeno beans, tomatoes, and soup.
In greased pan put one layer of meat mixture, Doritos, cheese.
Bake @ 400 degrees until cheese is golden.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put eggs in a large bowl; beat for 1 minute.
Add onions, green peppers, pimento, sugar, salt, butter and cream corn.
Slowly adding scalded milk, beat until well blended.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° moderately slow oven about 50 minutes.
This is really delicious.

title: vegetable snack
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl, mix well and chill.
Use as "mini snack" or garnish for main dishes.

title: apple cinnamon puffs
directions: Boil to a syrup the sugar, water and food coloring.
Peel and slice apples.
Place in a greased shallow 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Pour syrup over apples.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Partially cook the zucchini.
Drain and put into baking dish. Mix with all remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Dot all on top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ricotta cookies(10 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add Ricotta cheese and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Serve with sliced vegetables.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in an iron skillet. Boil 1 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup milk. Have both of these going at the same time. When sugar is brown, pour boiling mixture into the browned sugar and remove from stove. Add 2/3 stick oleo, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and salt. Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: italian chicken
directions: Skin chicken and soak overnight in dressing (covered completely).
Drain and bake in a foil-lined casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Chop vegetables
together;
drain.
Put
spices,
alum, sugar and vinegar together.
Bring
to
a boil; add vegetables and bring to a boil.	Boil for 15 minutes, pour into hot jars, seal.	Makes 5 pints.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine with chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, flour and baking powder alternately to chocolate mixture.
Do not overbeat.
Beat egg whites and fold gently into batter.
Add pecans and coconut.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick beef and gravy
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Remove from skillet and drain.
Follow directions on back of gravy mix.
When gravy thickens, add hamburger meat and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice, pasta, potatoes or anything you choose.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple and save liquid.
Add cold water to make 1 cup. Mix boiling water and jello well.
Stir in measured liquid and chill approximately 1 1/4 hours.
Stir in cool whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in oranges., pineapple, marshmallows, and coconut.
Spoon into 6 cup mold.
Chill 4 hours or until firm. Unmold.

title: graham yummies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil; cover with whole graham crackers placed as close together as possible.
In 1-quart saucepan, stir together butter and brown sugar until melted.
Boil for 3 minutes, then pour mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Watch carefully so they don't burn.
Cool for 15 minutes and break into pieces.

title: coconut-honey fruit dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Serve with bite-sized fruit pieces, melon balls, berries, etc.

title: kielbasa and veggies over linguini
directions: Put chicken broth and water in skillet over medium heat. Add zucchini, squash, onion and basil.
Cover; simmer until veggies become tender.
Add kielbasa.
Put on low.
Cook up linguini.
Drain.
Add kielbasa and veggies to linguini.
Serve in plates and enjoy.

title: microwave cheddary chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in dish; place chicken on top. Cover lightly with wax paper and cook on High 15 minutes.
Stir in rice mixture and continue cooking on High 10 minutes longer.

title: * chocolate delight-no bake cookies *
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and butter until soft ball stage (2 1/2 minutes).
Add vanilla, oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix first 5
ingredients.
Pour into an ovenproof dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: low-fat strawberry dessert
directions: Put cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix by hand.
Then add Cool Whip. Pour over cake. Mix strawberries (sliced) and glaze.
Pour over cream cheese. Let set. Refrigerate.

title: c-foam cider pie
directions: Heat 3/4 cup of the cider with candy red hots.
When candy is melted, add the gelatin and stir until dissolved; then stir in the remaining cider.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites; beat until foamy and frothy.
Fold in diced apples, and whipped cream.
Pour into the baked pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain well.
Mix chili con carne; spread in baking dish and spread sour cream on top of mixture.
Add layer of cheese on top of sour cream.
Crush Doritos and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: punch for 100
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O and Kool-Aid in the boiling water.
Add sugar and cold water.
Add lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.

title: grandma's cod
directions: Boil and drain cod.
Melt butter with oil and heat until bubbly.
Add garlic, salt and pepper; simmer.
Add cod.
Add flour to cold milk and shake well to remove lumps.
Add this to warmed milk and stir into simmering cod.
Continue to simmer a few minutes.
Serve hot with polenta.

title: cotton pickin cake
directions: Mix well and make 4 layers.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in a 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add all ingredients except flour. Mix flour in by hand.
Place greased side up, in greased bowl. Cover with damp cloth.
Refrigerate.
Can be refrigerated 5 days. Shape into rolls 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen medium rolls.

title: burger dogs
directions: Roll into shape of hot dog and wrap a slice of bacon around each one.
Broil 3 inches from heat until cooked.
Serve on a hot dog bun.

title: rib eye roast or tenderloin(pink in the middle)
directions: Rub the
roast all over with lemon pepper and olive oil and place
in
shallow	pan.
Preheat
oven
Put the roast in	the
oven
and	close
the
door.
Do not open for 2 hours. The
roast should be cooked 5 minutes a pound for rare and 6 to 7 minutes a pound for less pink.

title: easy crab cakes
directions: Combine egg with bread crumbs, mustard and mayonnaise, salt, and pepper.
Fold in crab meat and shape into cakes.
Coat with additional crumbs and refrigerate for one hour or until ready to cook.
Saute in butter (no substitute) over medium heat for about three minutes per side or until delicately browned.

title: silly salad
directions: Mix Jell-O (in dry form) with Cool Whip.
Chunk up peaches and add to Cool Whip and Jell-O.
Then add cottage cheese.
Stir all this up real well and put in refrigerator for about 1 hour and serve.

title: broccoli, rice and chicken casserole
directions: On bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan place uncooked Minute rice, then add soups and mix.
Drop pads of butter around to equal one stick.
Next add broccoli (thawed) and the cheese.
On top of all this, lay chicken breasts.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally (I remove chicken and stir every 15 minutes).
Can be made in the morning and stored in the refrigerator until evening when ready to bake.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Add enough flour to make stiff enough to roll out. Cut in desired shapes.

title: cauliflower custard
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions.
Drain well; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, sharp cheese, butter, parsley, minced onion, salt and pepper.
Arrange cauliflower in a 1-quart casserole dish; cover with egg mixture.
Top with buttered crumbs and remaining grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until custard is set.
Serves 4.

title: carolina delights
directions: Combine margarine, milk, cocoa and sugar in a saucepan and bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla and mix.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients together; pour into ovenproof casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's ginger cookies
directions: Roll out and cut.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix in flour, salt and soda. Add oats and nuts; stir well.
Drop by small spoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: party ice cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add milk and sugar to chocolate mixture and stir.
Add coconut.
Press in pan.
Let set in refrigerator a few minutes before adding filling.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix the fruit juices with 2 packages pudding and Tang.
Pour over fruit.
Top with coconut.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in 9 x 13 sprayed dish. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients together and dot with butter.
Bake until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean at 350°, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mark's vegetarian chili
directions: In large cooking pot, simmer oil, onion, carrot and tofu about 10 minutes.
Add granulated garlic for 1 minute.
I then drain and rinse beans.
Add beans, diced tomatoes, tomato juice and water to pot.
Increase heat to medium and bring to boil.
Add spices and reduce heat and let simmer 45 minutes.
Add miso and tamari sauce. Let simmer another 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Bon Appetite!

title: home canned apple pie filling
directions: Peel and slice apples;	place
in salt water to prevent discoloration.
Combine
remaining	ingredients
in a 12-quart stockpot.
Cook over
medium
heat	until
thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook for 2
to
minutes
longer; drain apples. Add to syrup.
Bring to boil; cook for 1 minute.
Spoon apples into hot
sterilized jars leaving 1-inch headspace.
Seal with 2 piece lids.
Process
in boiling water bath for 25 minutes. Yield: 6 to 7 quarts.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Pour over combined cauliflower, broccoli, grapes and 2 cheeses. Allow to sit in refrigerator 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: strawberry or peach pie
directions: Wash fruit and place in baked pie shell.
Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add jello; pour over fruit. Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple salad
directions: Wash apples and core; chop into small pieces, leaving on the skins for color.
Add lemon juice, celery, mayo and yogurt. Sprinkle on finely chopped cashews and mix thoroughly. Refrigerate before serving.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon, salt and paprika and let marinate overnight.
Roll chicken breasts in bread crumbs.
Drizzle with 1/4 cup margarine.
Cook 3/4 hour at 350°.
Drizzle last 1/4 cup margarine.
Bake another 1/4 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl as listed.
Delicious!!

title: toasted ravioli
directions: Dip ravioli in egg, then bread crumbs.
Deep fry in 1-inch of heated oil at 350° until golden brown, about 1 minute.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and serve.
May serve with spaghetti sauce on side for dipping.
Makes 20 ravioli.

title: krispy brownies
directions: Bake one Brownie Mix according to directions on the package, or use your own favorite brownie recipe.
As soon as you remove brownies from the oven, carefully spread marshmallow creme on the top, immediately frost with peanut butter, chocolate chips and Rice Krispies mixture.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in salt water and remove from bone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute celery, bell pepper and onion. Add can of mushrooms and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix with drained spaghetti.
Place in baking dish.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes just until hot.

title: spanish vegetables
directions: Cook Minute rice about 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and cook in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: leslie's soup
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add other ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.

title: pita sandwich spread
directions: Cook pilaf mix according to directions; cool.
Drain garbanzos.
Process all in food processor until smooth.
Correct seasoning.
Use in pita sandwiches with sliced tomatoes, sprouts, cucumber, cheese and dressing.

title: fruit sparkle(punch)
directions: Mix bananas, orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and water. Stir mixture thoroughly and freeze in refrigerator trays.
When ready to
serve,
fill
large glasses about 1/3 full of frozen mixture, then finish filling them with cold 7-Up or ginger ale. This makes about 35 glasses.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Place bouillon cubes in water. Bring to a boil. add vegetables. Simmer for 12 minutes until tender. In another saucepan melt butter and
blend in flour. Cook 1 min. Add milk and stir until thickens, approximately 10 min over low heat. Cut cheese into small chunks and melt in milk. Add vegetables and bouillon then simmer.

title: tony's dill pickles
directions: You will need 7 to 8 quart jars, clean.

title: pecan chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Mix egg yolks, milk, sugar and salt and cook in top of double boiler until it coats the spoon but not any longer.
Add gelatin and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar gradually.
Fold custard into egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts, saving a few to sprinkle on top.
Pour into cooked, cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: milk caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar, beating until thick enough to spread.

title: maple squares
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add 2 beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well and add flour and baking powder.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam or other cooking spray.
Press firmly.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Stir in the brown sugar and nuts and spread over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting in squares.

title: rich pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil gently for 5 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Place pecans in pie shell.
Mix eggs, vanilla and salt in a bowl.
Gradually stir in cooled syrup mixture.
Pour over pecans and the pie shell.
Place in preheated 375° oven.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Serves 8.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Quarter and boil potatoes.
Mash with onion, salt and pepper. Stir in diced eggs, mustard and mayonnaise to taste.

title: mashed potatoes with browned onions
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Melt 3 tablespoons of margarine in a large skillet.
Add onions and cook over medium-low heat for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Increase heat to medium and cook 5 to 7 minutes longer, stirring occasionally, until golden.
Drain potatoes, reserving 1 cup cooking water and return to pot.
Add reserved cooking water, remaining margarine, the salt and pepper.
Mash smooth with potato masher.
Stir in onions and parsley.

title: boston creme pie
directions: Split cake layer into two layers.
Prepare pudding as directed, except using 1 cup milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Spread bottom layer with pudding mixture; top with remaining layer.
Spread top with hot fudge topping.
Chill.
Preparation time: 15 minutes plus cooling.

title: chutney cheese spread
directions: Combine cheeses, sherry, curry and salt; blend well. Stir in chutney; chill. Turn into dish; top with chives. Serve with choice of crackers as a dip.

title: frozen or fresh vegetable casserole
directions: Place one package frozen vegetables in a cup of boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Boil just enough to thaw; drain.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Blend together chicken and celery soups.
Put half the butter, half the onions and half the soup on top of vegetables.
Proceed with second package and place remaining soup, onion and butter on top.
Place can of onion rings on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or put in microwave for 20 minutes on Medium heat.
Serves 8.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cook butter or margarine and syrup for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Place crackers one layer at a time and mixture between each layer.

title: melt-in-your-mouth sausages
directions: Put sausages in skillet and cover with water.
Simmer until done and drain.
Put rest of ingredients into a crock-pot.
Add sausages.
This can be served over spaghetti so cut sausages in chunks or can be served in a bun as a sandwich with sausages sliced.
Cover in crock-pot and cook on low for 4 hours.
Increase to high and cook 1 hour more.

title: sexy chicken
directions: Brown chicken and place in casserole pan which has been greased.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 or 3 hours, covered.
Uncover the last 15 minutes and garnish with slivered almonds.
Serve with rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tupperware cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and water.
Stir until moistened.
Add eggs and stir until blended.
Let stand while spreading pie filling in bottom of Tupperware 3-quart casserole with cone inserted.
Pour in cake mix.
Microwave cake 14 minutes on 100% power or until cake begins to shrink away from sides of casserole. Let stand for 20 minutes, then invert on serving plate.
You have a cherry topped chocolate cake.
Recipe can be used with apple pie filling and carrot cake mix (or spice cake mix).
Also German chocolate cake mix with coconut pecan frosting for a self frosted German chocolate cake.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add eggs, pumpkin and lemon juice. Mix well and pour onto a greased and floured jelly roll pan. Sprinkle pecans over top of mixture. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook the chicken.
Remove from bone and cut it up.
Dry bread in a slow oven, then cube.
Make gravy (medium thick) using the chicken broth.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cabbage and potatoes
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely.
Cut potatoes in 1-inch pieces.
Saute chopped onion and garlic in the oil.
Add all of the other ingredients.
Cook slowly, until done.
(More water may be added as necessary.)

title: angel biscuits
directions: Blend together flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir into batter.
Store in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight. Cut into biscuits and let rise.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones from chicken and cut or shred into small pieces.
Chop finely the hard-boiled eggs and add to chicken.
Peel and slice apples, cut into small pieces, then put apples and desired amount of pickle relish and blend finely. Add apples and relish to chicken mixture.
Mix in enough Miracle Whip, stirring along, until you get the right consistency.
Serve on lettuce or use for chicken salad sandwiches.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat margarine in a large bowl for 30 seconds.
Add 1 1/4 cups sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet; drain.
In large bowl, mix browned beef, corn, Miracle Whip, chili powder and salsa.
Stir until mixed well.
In baking dish, layer meat, chips and cheese for 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Pack cabbage tightly into quart jars.
Add salt and red pepper. Pour tap water over until full.
Seal and set aside to sour.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix and put into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce to 325° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and pimento cheese together thoroughly. Add a good dash or two of Accent. Add beef jerky and as much green onions as you like for your taste (I chop both the jerky and green onions real fine). I usually use about 1/2 jar of jerky and one bunch of green onions if the onions are not very big. Wrap and chill.

title: de de's chicken soup
directions: Rinse chicken thoroughly with cold water and place in pot with 6 quarts water and salt.
Bring to a boil, uncovered.
Prepare vegetables:
Peel onions and carrots.
Wash and cut celery.
After 1 hour, skim top foam off chicken stock and discard.
Add onions and celery.
Cover.
Continue to simmer for 3 hours.
Stir gently about once every hour (keep covered).
Add tomato sauce.
One hour later, add carrots.
Simmer carrots for one more hour or until tender (uncovered).

title: twisty beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Combine all ingredients except French fried onion rings.
Pour half the mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 can onions.
Pour remaining macaroni mixture over onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover; top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In large bowl, layer brownie pieces, mousse and Cool Whip. Top with Hersey bar pieces.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled for party size.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Place the cottage cheese in a blender and process until smooth; set aside.
Spray the inside of a medium skillet with nonstick vegetable cooking spray and place over high heat.
Add the chicken and saute, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add the stock and cook for 2 minutes, stirring often.
Add the milk and 1/3 cup of the blended cottage cheese to the skillet (refrigerate remaining cottage cheese for another use).
Cook, stirring for 3 minutes, or until the sauce begins to thicken, then add fettuccine and continue cooking until the sauce is the desired thickness.

title: caramel apples
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy saucepan and boil hard for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and dip apples. Makes about 20 medium sized apples.

title: mandarin orange bread
directions: Combine ingredients in this order; egg, sugar, oranges, flour, nuts,
soda and salt with electric mixer, adding enough reserved syrup to thin batter to pouring consistency.
Bake in a greased and
floured 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° until browned on top.

title: spiceless fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs; add fruit, nuts and all dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: artichoke and ranch dip
directions: Take hard leaves from artichoke and chop remaining leaves. Prepare dip and mix with chopped artichoke.
Serve with vegetable assortment.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point.
Add sugar.
Add orange jello, dissolve and cool.
Add 2 cups buttermilk.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese; add egg.
Add sugar and beat with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over crust.

title: tuna cobb salad pockets
directions: In medium bowl, combine oil, ReaLemon brand, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire and garlic powder; pour over tuna.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pita bread.
Serve in pita bread.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir all ingredients, except the green chilies and cheese. Pour 1/2 the batter into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Spread chilies and cheese over batter.
Pour remaining batter over all. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until set. Serve with spoon. Serves 6 to 8.

title: crunch munch apples
directions: Cut the apples in quarters; spread the peanut butter on the apples.
Sprinkle raisins on top.

title: chicken cutlet l'orange
directions: Arrange chicken cutlets in baking dish, sprinkling them with garlic and onion powder.
On first layer, spread marmalade. Arrange second layer, sprinkle with garlic and onion powder and spread with marmalade.
Mix wine with orange juice and pour over cutlets.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: duncan hines peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with fork dipped in water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa then egg yolks and milk.
Thicken on top of stove in saucepan.
Add butter and vanilla; pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.
Beat the egg whites.
Add a dash of cream of tartar and 1/4 teaspoon sugar.
Cover with meringue.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Enjoy.

title: no fat pumpkin bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except flours.
Stir in rye flour.
Stir in enough all-purpose flour, 1 cup at a time, to make dough easy to handle. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; gently roll in flour to coat.
Knead about 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
(Dough will be soft.)
Spray a large bowl with nonstick cooking spray. Place dough in bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place about 1 1/4 hours or until double.

title: vermont maple cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar well. Add eggs. Stir in flavorings and sour cream. Add flour, soda and salt. Blend well. Add nuts. Chill, if soft.
Heat oven to 375°. Drop by spoonfuls on greased sheet and bake about 10 minutes or until done.
Frost with Maple Butter Glaze.

title: italian egg biscuits(lemon cookies)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Make a well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with hands until dough is smooth and forms a ball.
If dough is sticky, add more flour.
Take small amounts of dough (the size of a walnut) and roll into balls (flour hands to prevent sticking).
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake at 375° until light brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.
Frost with a Confectioners Sugar Icing.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, gradually add cornmeal, butter and salt into boiling water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolk with milk; gradually stir into cornmeal mixture.
Mix flour with sugar and baking powder.
Add to cornmeal mixture; beat until well blended.
Fold in egg whites. Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Spoon from casserole and serve hot with butter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup of butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Crush cornflakes and stir in remaining butter. Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and soda. Chop in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast. Stir well.
Keep covered in refrigerator at least 1 hour or better.
Will keep 1 week.
Flour hands.
Pinch off enough dough to roll into biscuits.
Place on greased pan and let rise 1 or 2 hours.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Heat 4 cups water.
Dissolve cheese and marshmallows in water with electric mixer.
Add dry Jell-O.
After it has cooled some, add pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Stir and put in refrigerator until firmly set.

title: wake up casserole
directions: Place hash brown patties in a single layer in a greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer, or until edges are golden brown and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, sifted dry ingredients, butter and corn. Drop by spoonfuls into heated frying pan. Fry until brown and done through.

title: crab salad(appetizer)
directions: Add chopped crab meat to the next 4 ingredients and mix.
Add mayonnaise; mix, adding more mayonnaise if needed.
Serve with crackers as an appetizer.
Serves 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg yolks, then alternate adding flour with the milk.
(Put extract in milk and stir it before adding the milk.)

title: old-fashioned doughnuts
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
so dough is thick enough to roll out, soft but not tough.
Roll out on well floured surface to 1/8
inch thickness. Cut in 2 x 4-inch or smaller rectangular shapes,
slit in center and pull one end through center slit. Deep
fry to a light brown color on both sides.
Sprinkle with granulated
sugar while hot.
Put on paper toweled platter and enjoy.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef.
Add paste, water, enchilada sauce, chili and beans.
Line dish with tortillas.
Place in layers beginning with mix cheese, olives and tortillas.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: arlene's oven mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until done.
Drain.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add butter, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Add milk slowly while mixing.
Beat until smooth.
Spread potato mixture in a greased 8 x 8-inch or 9-inch glass pan. Sprinkle with paprika; dot with butter.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap.
May be made up to a week ahead.
When needed, bake in a 350° oven about 40 minutes.
Take a fork and run it across the top to make it look pretty before you bake it.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bible cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add oil and beat well.
Add honey slowly while beating; beat well.
Add rest of ingredients, except raisins, and beat well.
Add raisins and stir.
Bake at 350° in 8 x 10-inch greased and floured pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: double cheese delight
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
In large skillet, cook meat, onion and celery until browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and noodles.
Pour into an ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butternut cake
directions: Fold in tablespoon butter flavoring.
Start in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in pineapple and pie filling
Add nuts.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups candies; reserve remaining for decorations.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chopped candies and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Immediately press 3 reserved candies on top of each.
Cool.

title: cold corn salad
directions: Chop everything fine, the size of the corn.
Refrigerate.

title: reese cups
directions: Stir and
press
in oblong pan.
Melt 6 ounces chocolate chips with 1/4 stick margarine and pour over mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper lightly. Add rest of ingredients and cook until vegetables are done. Add 1 cup of macaroni and cook about 20 minutes until macaroni is done.
Makes a large kettle and freezes well.

title: walnut torte("my favorite dessert")
directions: Crush soda crackers to fine crumbs; set aside.
Beat egg whites until firm.
Add sugar and baking powder.
Mix.
Add soda cracker crumbs, nuts and vanilla to egg white mixture; fold together.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Slice as you would a pie and serve with whipped cream topping.

title: warm potato salad
directions: In one bowl, combine potatoes and eggs. In a separate bowl, combine all other ingredients, then mix all together. Best when served warm.

title: frozen cheese torte
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: no refrigerator sugar cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs, then add vanilla.
Slowly stir in dry ingredients, roll and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Flour chicken breasts and lightly brown in vegetable oil. Pour off excess oil and add the onion, pepper and mushrooms. Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste. Pour the tomato sauce and cheese soup in a bowl to mix. Then pour the tomato sauce over the chicken and vegetables. Continue to cook on the stove top about 30 to 40 minutes on mid temperature until chicken is done and vegetables are tender. Serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat until well mixed.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add to shortening mixture.
Add bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: coconut cheese cake
directions: In small bowl combine first 3 ingredients.
Press into bottom or 9-inch spring-form pan; set aside.

title: sparkling berry mint sipper
directions: Stir together cranberry raspberry juice and lemon juice. Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Add raspberries; pour over ice.
To serve, garnish with mint leaves.

title: tofu quiche
directions: Mix together tofu and eggs with mixer.
Steam vegetables and mix all ingredients together in bowl.
This makes about two quiches.
Pour ingredients int pie shells and sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and top with the melted margarine and crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a
2-quart
saucepan
mix
the
first 4 ingredients; bring to a
boil,
remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Drop by	teaspoon onto wax paper and cool.
These freeze well!

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water and mix until dissolved.
Add ice cream and heat until dissolved.
Add fruits and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serve.

title: cranberry preserves
directions: Bring to boil and simmer until foam clears (15 to 20 minutes). Stir constantly.
Cool 1 hour and add walnuts.
Pour into jars. Makes approximately 3 pints.

title: pecan fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, heat sugar, cocoa, butter, milk, and salt over low heat stirring until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spread mixture quickly in buttered 9 x 5 loaf pan. Cool, cut into squares. Makes 2 dozen.

title: blushing apple cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients and mix well. Add apples and stir gently to mix.
Pour into a pastry-lined pie plate.
Roll out remaining crust to fit top of pie.
Cut slits in top crust.
Place over apples.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until pastry is golden and apples are tender.

title: million dollar sugar cookies
directions: Mix; roll into balls.
Dip into sugar and press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes until light brown.

title: golden cheese bake
directions: Combine rice, carrots, 1 1/2 cups cheese, milk, eggs, onion and seasonings. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut eggplant into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Saute onion, green pepper and ground beef until beef loses its pink color.
Add corn.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Add eggplant, egg, salt and oregano and ground pepper.
Mix well.
Add cheese.
Spoon mixture into baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: banana split pie
directions: Crust: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine graham crackers and sugar. Add margarine. Mix well. Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate. Bake 10 minutes and cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 6 hours before using. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chicken with herbs and orange
directions: Note:
All these herbs are very easy to grow!
Try it!

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown green pepper in margarine in skillet.
Remove and set aside. Brown steak, mushrooms and garlic in pan drippings. Add oregano, catsup, sherry and 1 tomato.
Steam, covered, until meat is tender. Add remaining 2 tomatoes, green pepper, salt and pepper. Cook until just heated. Serve with rice.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Rinse and cut a thin slice from the stem end of each pepper. Remove white fiber and seeds.
Rinse cavities.
Drop into boiling water and cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove peppers from water and drain.
Saute the meat, onion and chopped pepper.
Cook until slightly tender.
Add uncooked rice, seasonings, tomato sauce and water.
Heat to a simmer, until rice is slightly tender.
Fill peppers with the meat mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 minutes.
If desired, top with bread crumbs and bake 10 - 15 minutes longer.

title: sadd cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix everything together.
Pour into lightly greased and floured pan (13 x 9 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in your preheated oven.
Let the cake cool for 10 to 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together in skillet. Drain fat. Add green chilies and rice, stirring to mix well.
Pour half of the mixture in a casserole dish. Add the grated cheese. Spread out over mixture. Add remaining mixture over cheese. Add bread crumbs to top.
Put into oven to brown crumbs at approximately 350°. Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well and mash out into the bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package direction making two 8 x 9-inch layers.
Cook according to box directions.

When layers of cake are completely cool, split in half horizontally to make four layers. Try to cut as evenly as possible to avoid being lop-sided. While cake is cooking, combine sugar, sour cream and coconut with the whipped topping and chill.
Before putting cake together, reserve one cup of sour cream mixture for sides of cake. Brush off any loose crumbs to keep from getting into the topping. Spread on top of each layer and sides.
Seal cake in an air tight container and place in refrigerator.
Best and more moist if cake sets for three days before serving.
Super simple and sooooo good!!!

title: city chicken
directions: Thread veal or pork cubes onto short skewers.
Combine crumbs and seasonings.
Combine egg and milk.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Brown slowly on all sides in hot shortening. Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add to meat, cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes.

title: avocado bean dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl and add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
In a large, shallow (glass preferably) dish, spread bean dip.
Cover with avocado mixture.
Next spread with sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with onions and ripe olives. Cover with cheese and serve with corn chips for dipping.

title: pam's german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut mixture.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar. Spoon over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese olive spread
directions: Blend together the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in pecans, salad olives, olive juice and pepper; do not add any salt. Mix well.
This filling will, at first, be slightly mushy.
After a few hours of refrigeration, it will be of spreading consistency. Keeps well up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll into small balls. Bake at 450° on broiler pan until brown.
Drain on paper towels. May be made ahead and frozen, but reheat before serving.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Save the graham cracker box to put the cake in.

title: dottie's bread stuffing
directions: Saute bacon in large skillet until almost crisp.
Add onion; cook until bacon is crisp and onion is soft.
Stir in poultry seasoning, celery salt, garlic salt and onion salt.
Put cubed bread in large bowl.
Pour bacon mixture and egg over it.
Mix until well blended, using 2 forks.
Add chicken stock to make a very moist but not wet mixture.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in melted butter for 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Add scallops, sour cream and parsley.
Place in casserole, top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: fish stew
directions: Cut up onions and cook in oil or fatback until done.
May add a little water to keep from sticking.
Add condensed tomato soup, then tomato juice.
May use all soup or all juice and add catsup to thicken.
Salt fish lightly before putting into stew.
Add black pepper generously.
Add sugar if too sharp.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Let come to a boil and then add fish and boil again.
Cut down heat and let simmer (cooking time will depend on size of fish).
When fish becomes flaky, stew is done.
Will serve about 15 people.

title: ding bats
directions: Mix dates and sugar with melted butter and cook over low heat until dissolved, stirring constantly. Pour over Rice Krispies and pecans.
Roll into balls and then roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix the
flour	and salt; cut in shortening.
Add water and mix.
Roll	out
1/4 inch thick to fit a 1 1/2 quart dish. Cut into 4
triangles.	Bake on cookie sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yum, yum chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Break into small pieces and layer in baking dish.
Pour cream of chicken over chicken breasts. Layer stuffing, then add butter (melted) and broth over stuffing. Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: easy penuche frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir over low heat 2 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in confectioners sugar.
Place pan of frosting in bowl of ice and water.
Beat until of spreading consistency.
If frosting is too stiff, heat slightly, stirring constantly.
Fills and frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or frosts a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Batter will be thick.
Spread out on hot griddle.

title: brady isd delicious cookies
directions: Cream together in a 30-quart mixer the first 3 ingredients. Add eggs to mixture.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Add oats and coconut; mix well.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Beat only enough to blend.
Place 5 rows by 7 rows on an 18 x 26 x 1-inch sheet pan, using a #30 scoop.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Yields 525 cookies.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Put large skillet on grill.
Let skillet get hot.
Put 1/4 of the bottle teriyaki sauce in skillet.
Slice steak at angle and place the sliced garlic into the cuts in the steak.
Place steak into hot skillet and turn often until steak is the way you like it.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine.
Add eggs and blend well. Add sugar.
Slowly add flour to mixture.
Beat well.
Add flavorings until blended.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook in well-greased Bundt pan for 90 minutes.
Check with toothpick until it comes out clean.

title: stir-fried beef
directions: Freeze meat 1 hour to firm to make slicing easier; slice into thin strips.
In small bowl, combine soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch; mix well.
In large skillet over high heat, cook pepper and onion in oil until tender-crisp.
Add meat mixture; stir fry until meat loses its pink color and sauce thickens slightly.
Add tomatoes; heat through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Mix butter and shortening.
Cream brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, soda and baking powder. Blend oatmeal, coconut, chocolate chips, cornflakes and M&M's. Drop by 1/4 cup measuring cup.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour pineapple in pan and spread evenly.
Add cherry pie filling and cover pineapple as much as possible.
Crumble dry cake mix over fruit fillings.
Sprinkle the walnuts over top and place butter slices on top of nuts, evenly over entire cake.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or longer until cooked.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips, sugar and milk. Stir to mix.
Let cool slightly, then beat in the egg yolks, 1 at a time, and add vanilla.
Whip the egg whites until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into baked pie crust and chill thoroughly.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add nuts, raisins and cut gum slices.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven in greased, paper-lined pan.

title: okinawa salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shake well.
Great over tossed salads.

title: rainbow girls favorite punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add pineapple juice.
Place in punch bowl.
Add pineapple and sherbet.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until clear.
Stir in jello. Let cool.
Place fresh strawberries into the baked pie shell. Pour jello mixture over the berries.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: roach bait
directions: Add lemon juice to milk to make buttermilk.

title: pizza casserole
directions: You will need 1 large baking dish.

title: hominy stuffing
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and broth mix; stir and cook until onion is transparent. Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until top is golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked spicy rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Stir well and bake, uncovered, 15 additional minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: noodles
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll thin and cut into noodles.
Let dry.

title: chicken brunswick stew
directions: Brown chicken and onions in oil.
Add tomatoes and water. Simmer 1 hour.
Remove chicken.
When cool, remove bones and cut up chicken.
Add chicken back to pot and add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Remove from heat and dissolve jello in pineapple.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip; fold in well.
Add buttermilk and nuts.
Refrigerate all day or overnight.

title: strawberry pie(6 servings)
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 2 tablespoons sugar until well blended.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes; allow to cool.
In a saucepan, mix 1 cup sugar, Jell-O, water, cornstarch and a dash of salt.
Bring to boil; boil slowly for 5 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Add the sliced strawberries. Pour into pie shell; refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mustard
directions: Blend - Cook in double boiler until custard like.
Keep refrigerated because of eggs.
Can - Seal when hot.

title: college kid casserole
directions: Start with 2 cups of macaroni and boil until soft, about 10 minutes.
Then drain.
Chop cheese into cubes.
Chop onions. Drain tuna well and remove from can in shreds, not chunks.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Mix together and then add macaroni while hot. Put into casserole dish and pack in if needed.
Then salt and pepper top.
Add butter, cubed, to top and push bread crumbs into top with fingers.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a saucepan and heat until blended and smooth.
Pour on chicken and baste.

title: cabbage creole
directions: Melt butter in 10 or 12-inch skillet; add all ingredients and mix well. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender (approximately 10 minutes), stirring occasionally. Do not overcook. Serves 8.

title: four layer pie
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°. Cool good.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello, water and 2 tablespoons sugar. Let jell.
When jelled, add pineapple and blueberries. After setting, top with sour cream, cream cheese and powdered sugar.

title: cherry whip(country:  american)
directions: Mix together and put in a freezer container (oblong approximately 14 inches long, 4 inches wide and 3 inches deep, with lid).
Tupperware celery keeper is perfect.
Freeze.
Makes a light dessert.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: delicious sandwiches
directions: Fry fresh hamburger or sausage until done.
Drain off liquid. If canned meat is used, take it out of jars and cut into chunks. Grind pickles and onions, then mix meat, pickles, onions, cheese and salad dressing together.
Spread bread with salad dressing mixture.
Now put another slice on top.
Beat eggs and milk.
Dip both sides of bread in this and brown well in skillet.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Wipe ribs with a damp paper towel.
Bake on rack in shallow pan at 450° for 35 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in pot and cook until slightly thickened.
Remove rack from roasting pan; drain grease.
Put ribs in bottom of pan; pour sauce over ribs. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corned beef dish
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Cube potatoes.
Cook all in large skillet, turning once or twice.
(Layer ingredients in skillet in order given.
Cook until potatoes are tender.) I use an electric skillet.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Spread in 9 x 13 greased and floured pan. Next mix remaining ingredients. Spread on top of first layer.
Garnish with nuts if desired. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, egg, juice and warm water.
Add peel, nutmeats, flour and baking powder.
Fold in cherries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool.

title: prune bread
directions: Sift first 8 ingredients together; set aside.
Combine sugar, shortening and eggs; add juice and prunes.
Blend in dry ingredients. Add nuts.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake in 2 well-greased small loaf pans in medium oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: triple decker strawberry cake
directions: Bake at 350°, center rack in oven; use 3 x 9.

title: cornish hen and wild rice stuffing
directions: Prepare rice as on directions of package.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Combine rice, onion, apple and egg and other seasonings.
Stuff the hens with rice and 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed. Mix well. Pour into prepared muffin tins. Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Mix tapioca with tomato sauce and juice.
Put all ingredients into large casserole or Dutch oven.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°.
Makes 6 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cut off beet tops, leaving 1-inch of stem.
Also leave root. Wash beets; cover with boiling water and cook until tender. Remove skins and slice beets.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar, salt, syrup and peanuts.
Cook on High 4 minutes. Remove.
Stir, then cook 4 more minutes on High.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda quickly; stir until light and foamy.
Pour into a lightly greased cookie sheet very thin.
When completely cool, break into pieces and store in an airtight container.
Do not double.

title: frozen yum yums
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Add egg yolks, chocolate, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and put graham cracker crumbs on bottom.
Pour on filling and freeze 2 hours.
Spread ice cream on top; sprinkle with crumbs.
Freeze.

title: fettuccine primavera
directions: Blanch the broccoli and cauliflower in boiling water.
Drain and set aside.
Heat the butter in a saucepan.
Saute the onion, carrot and mushrooms until tender.
Add flour and stir. Cook for 2 minutes.
Add the cream, broccoli and cauliflower.
Reduce to a simmer.

title: creamy dill veggie dip
directions: Place cream cheese, milk, dressing mix and dill weed in blender and blend until smooth. Store, tightly sealed, in refrigerator. Serve dip with vegetables and breadsticks.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly; shape firmly into loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with tomato slices and 1 1/2 cups shredded mild cheese.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: mother's chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate squares and oleo.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Pour into a greased oblong pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: busy day oven stew
directions: Put stew beef in a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add onion, carrots and potatoes.
Pour tomato soup over top.
Cover tightly and bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: nutty buddy pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, milk, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shells.
Freeze one hour.
Sprinkle with syrup and peanuts.
Refreeze.

title: walnut banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: sweet check mix
directions: Mix together and spread on cookie sheet first 3 ingredients. Melt butter, sugar and Karo syrup.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over mixture and mix to coat.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes.
Stir; bake 10 more minutes.
Cool on grocery bag.

title: sparkling berry-mint sipper
directions: In a 2-quart pitcher, stir together the chilled juice cocktail and the lemon juice.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Add the fresh raspberries.

title: marshmallow strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk in a double boiler.
Cool and blend in the whipped cream and the strawberries.
Put in a large flat glass dish and sprinkle with cookie or graham cracker crumbs. (Put the crumbs on the bottom.) Chill.
Enjoy.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, oil, eggs, flour, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add salt, baking soda, baking powder and rolled oats.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in walnuts.
Spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: grandma dickrell's molasses cake - 1936
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° in greased loaf pan for 35 minutes.

title: dad's meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients well; shape into small to medium size balls.
Brown on all sides in skillet in olive oil.
Cook in favorite tomato sauce recipe.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup and mayonnaise; prepare stuffing according to instructions on package.
Layer broccoli, chicken, sauce and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash large firm cucumbers and put them in a gallon glass jar. Mix together salt, pickling spice, alum and vinegar; pour over cucumbers.
Fill jar with water and put lid on.
Let set 60 days at room temperature.
It can stand longer.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Turn on oven and set at 350°.
Mix in a 1 1/2-quart bowl all ingredients.
With 2 teaspoons, drop mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until cookies are slightly puffed but still soft.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: crispy marshmallow bars
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in large, plastic mixing bowl in microwave for 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla and mix well.
Pour in cereal until evenly coated.
Press in cake pan and refrigerate until cool.

title: strawberry cloud
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice until creamy.
Add fresh strawberries and mix well.
Pinch sponge cake into bite-size pieces and add to the mix.
Mix well.
Chill for 6 hours.

title: wine and cheese muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups, or grease entire baking cup generously.
Mix baking mix, wine, oil and egg with fork.
Beat vigorously 30 strokes. Stir in remaining ingredients. Divide batter evenly among cups. Bake about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 1 dozen muffins, 150 calories per muffin.

title: broiled potato chips(low-fat)
directions: Wash and thinly slice the potatoes.
Mix the oil and the soy sauce and whisk until blended.
Using either a pastry brush or a spray bottle, brush or spray the slices on both sides lightly. Lay the slices on a baking sheet.
Do not overlap.
Broil at the middle level for 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn and broil for 3 to 5 more minutes until golden.
Broiling time will vary, so watch the chips.
Dark chips will be bitter.
Season to taste, if desired.
If made in advance, chips can be reheated in the oven.

title: holiday hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients except lemon slices in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serve at once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruity salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O into Cool Whip and mix.
Add cottage cheese, drained fruit cocktail and nuts.

title: crock-pot cheese dip
directions: Melt in microwave or double boiler the Velveeta cheese and cream cheese.
Fry and drain the hamburger.
Mix the hamburger, cheeses and salsa in crock-pot; simmer until ready to eat.

title: pecan bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir by hand.
Makes 2 loaves. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together like crumbs.
Save 1 1/4 cups for topping
To remaining crumbs, add buttermilk and baking soda.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cheeses.
Place dip in an ungreased casserole.
Put shredded cheese on top and bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or dip size Fritos.

title: ice cream
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk; heat, but do not boil.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add enough half and half to fill can.
This is for a 1-gallon hand turned or electric freezer.

title: cheese straws #1
directions: Cream
cheese and butter with hands until smooth.
Then work in dry ingredients until firm dough is made.
Run through star-shaped cookie press.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: glazed chicken breasts
directions: Place 5 to 6 large boneless chicken breasts in baking dish. Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chunky chicken salsa sandwiches
directions: In large bowl combine chicken, yogurt, salsa and cumin; stir gently.
Stir in pepper, cilantro and green onions.
Line pita half with lettuce.
Spoon chicken salad mix evenly into pockets. Sprinkle toppings over chicken salad mix.
Serve immediately. When using nonfat yogurt, drain excess liquid by placing yogurt in a coffee filter for 5 minutes.

title: egg rolls(cut down from recipe for 500, khame thene chantavong)
directions: You can
freeze
of the mixture for later and just make 1/3.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak the beans overnight.
Put half into bean pot.
Put the salt pork in center, then put the rest of the beans on top.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, mustard, molasses and 6 cups cold water. Cover and put in an oven at 325° for 8 hours, adding more water when necessary.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly (at least one minute at creaming speed).
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until creamy. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with a tumbler that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: artichoke heaven
directions: Mix all ingredients together until artichoke hearts fall apart and are well blended.
Bake in buttered casserole at 450° for 30 minutes or until top is nicely browned.
Serve with Stone Wheat crackers while warm.

title: simple biscuits
directions: Put flour in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of it.
Add shortening and milk to well.
Mix well and roll out on floured surface.
Cut out small biscuits (small juice can works well). Bake in a 425° oven until golden brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except wax and morsels.
If still dry, add extra half stick butter.
Form into balls.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet with a toothpick in each ball.
Freeze overnight. Next day, grate wax and melt in a double boiler together with chocolate morsels.
Dip frozen balls into chocolate.
When dried, remove toothpick and enjoy!

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Separate crescent rolls into two pieces.
Flatten and pinch together seams.
Brush pepperoni stick with egg yolk and cover with flour.
Place on flattened rolls and tuck ends under.
Repeat with second pepperoni stick and remaining half of rolls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool about 5 minutes and slice into 1-inch pieces.

title: chimichangas
directions: Sprinkle salt in a medium skillet and place over medium heat. Add beef, garlic and spices.
Cook and stir with a fork until meat crumbles and loses its pink color.
Stir in remaining filling ingredients, remove from heat and cool.

title: candy apple pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup apple juice and cornstarch until thickened.
Pour over apples and let simmer another 2 minutes or so.
Set aside to cool, then pour into a graham cracker pie crust. Put in refrigerator to cool.
May top with Cool Whip and a sprinkle of cinnamon when ready to serve.

title: hamburger dills
directions: Cut pickles in 1/4-inch slices and pack into quart jars with 2 pieces of celery and 2 pieces of dill and some onion slices in each jar.
Broil syrup and pour hot over pickle slices in jar. Seal.
Let cure at least 30 days before eating.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions in greased pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, (15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute by hand beater).
Pour into plate and bake until brown.
Can also add turkey, chicken, broccoli, mushrooms or spinach.

title: veggie surprise
directions: Place crushed crackers, cooked broccoli and cauliflower in large casserole dish and give it a toss.
Then cut up cheese and toss through mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over and pat margarine on top around casserole.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: marian's christmas candy
directions: Melt the morsels in top of a double boiler.
Add other ingredients and stir.
When well mixed, drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool about 1 hour.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine and heat soup with seasonings and broth, mixing well. Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with chips, then layer of chicken, half of sauce and half of cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: unbelievable oat bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
In a separate large bowl, mix wet ingredients.
Combine wet and dry mixtures with mixer. Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 30.

title: roast beef
directions: Rub beef with vinegar.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic salt and paprika.
Brown in roaster (uncovered) at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Add water and cover meat with onion.
Lower oven to 300 degrees, cover and bake another 4-5 hours.
For a smaller roast, cook about 2 1/2 hours to 3 hours (approximately 1 hour per pound).
Cool and thinly slice, then reheat in juice.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine in casserole dish and bake uncovered at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: kielbasa appetizers
directions: *Really start out with small amount, to your taste.
Same applies to apricot preserves.

title: blueberry trifle
directions: Cut pound cake into 1/2-inch cubes and layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon over prepared vanilla pudding, spreading evenly. Layer second pound cake cubes and spoon lemon pudding evenly.
Top with blueberries.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut raw chicken into cubes.
Cook at medium high in butter until slightly brown and almost done.
Add cream of chicken soup and about 3/4 can of water.
Mix well.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Add carrots; cook 5 minutes.
Turn down to medium low heat.
Cover and cook until carrots are almost done, stirring occasionally.
Add peas; cook about 10 minutes.
Add dumpling mixture in spoonfuls on top. Cover and cook for 12 minutes.
Do not lift lid until 12 minutes is up.
Serve stew on top of dumplings.

title: zucchini nut bread
