directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend contents of the 2 bowls.
Blend in mixture of grated zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger - spaghetti bake
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
In a 4-quart casserole dish, place hamburger, cooked spaghetti, soups, milk and cheese.
Mix well and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice banana into large mixing bowl, beat until well mashed. Add remaining ingredients; blend.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan, at least 15 minutes.
Remove from pan, finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: tomato chili
directions: You will need 1 cloth bag.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake until golden brown. Bake at 350° in a preheated oven.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and mash with sour cream and cream cheese. Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Sprinkle jello over fruit cocktail. Mix with remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg, applesauce and raisins. Add flour mixture.
Stir, just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)

title: lo-cal salad dressing
directions: Add dressing mix to yogurt until you get the taste you desire. Use on tossed salad or baked potato.

title: good and easy chicken pot pie
directions: Simmer chicken breast about 30 minutes in a covered pan with next 3 ingredients and 2 cups of water.
When tender, drain (reserving broth).
Remove skin and bone.
Chop meat into large pieces.
Remove skin and bone.
Chop meat into large pieces.
In 11 x 7-inch baking dish, pour soup and thin with 1/2 cup of broth. Season with salt and pepper; stir in chicken, carrots and peas. Top with roll dough, unrolled but not separated.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown and filling is bubbling, about 25 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls. Mix 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Roll balls in mixture. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until set.
Cool.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: italian sausage
directions: Cut cabbage into 8 sections.
Quarter potatoes.
Cut Italian sausage into 5-inch pieces in large baking dish.
Pour 1/4 cup water over.
Layer cabbage, potatoes and sausage.
Pour olive oil and vegetable oil over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and cook for 20 minutes more to brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, flour, gelatin, oil and water.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add berries and beat three minutes or until creamy.
Bake in a large oblong pan or three layer pans for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool completely before frosting.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Thoroughly mix the first four ingredients.

Gradually add in the sifted dry ingredients. When well blended, fold in 3/4 cup chopped walnuts and 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate morsels. Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool for 20 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Dust with powdered sugar just before serving.

title: bologna-roni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and combine with macaroni.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: crinkle molasses cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Sift together next 4 ingredients. Combine.
Roll in balls (walnut size); dip tops in sugar.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Flatten each with a glass dipped in water.
Bake at 350° (will crinkle on top when baked).

title: pineapple cupcakes
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add pineapple and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately.
Fill cupcake pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken sandwich
directions: Place chicken slices on toast.
Cook other ingredients until cheese is melted.
Pour over chicken.

title: spanish tostadas
directions: Get a small frying pan, put over medium heat.
Put 1/2 cup of oil in the frying pan.
Put one corn tortilla in the pan.
Fry the tortilla until it gets hard, then turn the tortilla over until it gets hard.
Take it out.
Put it on top of a plate.
Make about four of them.

title: sandy's cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, milk and oregano in bowl.
Chill, covered, until slightly firm.
Shape mixture into ball; roll in parsley to coat.
Serve with crackers or Melba toast rounds.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine the egg, vinegar, sugar, flour and reserved pineapple juice in a saucepan and heat on medium until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and let cool, then fold in the Cool Whip.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate. Sprinkle reserved nuts on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to package.
Add chicken, soup, milk, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook in microwave (Medium-high) for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Crumble over chicken mixture to form crust.
Cook over Medium-high for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: microwave onion pie(vidalia)
directions: Mix crackers and margarine and press into a 10-inch deep dish glass pie pan.
Place onions with butter in a microwave dish and microwave for 5 to 7 minutes on High.
In small bowl, mix milk and eggs.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Top with cheese. Microwave 4 minutes.
Turn and microwave 4 minutes more. Sometimes it takes 3 to 4 minutes to set up middle.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and cream potatoes. Add butter, sugar, milk, eggs, flour and vanilla. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. They freeze real good in 1-gallon freezer bags.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine and in mixing bowl combine it with the whole kernel corn (with juice), cream-style corn, beaten eggs and corn muffin mix.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add shredded cheese and bake until it melts, approximately 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch or larger (10 x 14-inch preferably) pan. Open cans of fruit and pour in pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over fruit, then nut meats on top of cake mix.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (blueberries about 50 minutes) or until brown.

title: tomato-mozzarella salad
directions: Cut tomatoes in quarters, cut cheese in small slices and add olive and vinegar dressing, salt and pepper and basil leaves. Toss and serve.
Serves 4.

title: fruit sauces
directions: Blend pineapple, coconut milk, sugar and run in food processor until smooth.
Spoon over sherbet or ice cream.
Makes about 2 3/4 cups.

title: beef with sour cream
directions: Cut meat into thin strips. Dredge in flour with spices. Use large skillet and quickly brown meat in hot oil. Add rest of the ingredients. Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in sour cream. Heat, but do not boil. Serve over hot rice.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture. Next, add berries and vanilla and mix until all is well blended. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lower fat cranberry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and margarine, add eggs and continue beating until well mixed.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, beat until well mixed.
Stir in orange juice and peel by hand.
Spoon 1/2 of batter into pan.
Spread 1/2 of cranberry sauce on top of batter. Repeat layer of batter and cranberry sauce.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing pan.

title: hungarian goulash soup
directions: Saute onions in bacon fat.
Add bell peppers and paprika. Saute beef shoulder until golden.
Add to onions in saute pan. Add beef stock.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add diced potatoes and cook. Serves 10.

title: caramel
directions: In a medium saucepan mix sugar and light corn syrup.
Boil over low to medium heat until medium ball stage.
Add rest of ingredients and boil until firm ball stage.
Pour into a greased square pan.
Cut into squares when cool with a greased knife.

title: hamburger beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix all ingredients together. Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cook, uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Make a paste of the cocoa and coloring; add to the mixture. Combine salt, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add alternately with the flour.
Beat well.
Do not beat, but fold in vinegar and soda, mixing well.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 350°.

title: raisin-bread stuffing
directions: In large saucepan, saute onions and celery in butter for 3 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Cook 2 minutes and set aside.
Grate 4 teaspoons orange peel from oranges.
Squeeze oranges to make 2 cups orange juice or add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir in orange peel, basil, allspice, pepper and salt to walnut mixture. Place bread crumbs in large bowl.
Add juice and vegetable mixture. Toss to mix.
Use 4 to 5 cups to stuff 8 to 10 pound turkey.
Make balls (1/4 cupfuls) of remaining mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use as appetizers.

title: zucchini burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into patties.
Heat 4 minutes on each side over medium heat.
Top with cheese; cook until melted. Serve on buns.
Makes 4 burgers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer in a large pan.
Bake at 425° (covered) until tender.

title: broccoli lasagna(low cholesterol)
directions: In a bowl combine broccoli, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and sugar.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 cup tomato mixture. Arrange 1/4 uncooked noodles over sauce.
Top with 1/4 tomato mixture; then 1/4 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat noodle, tomato and cheese layers 3 more times.
Cover and allow to set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours to soften noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese is lightly browned.
Serves 12.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order and bake at 320 degrees for approximately 1 hour in tube pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Place in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Use 2 (8-inch) pies, one deep dish 10-inch pie or 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 9 x 11-inch.
Spread pie filling into oiled pan.
In mixing bowl, stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend in softened butter and egg, stirring to make a thick batter.
Drop batter from spoon and spread to cover filling.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are bubbly and top browned.
I like cherry or blueberry best.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk.
Spoon into pie shell.
Slice bananas over cream cheese mixture.
Add pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add cherries or nuts, if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first six ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir only until all is moist.
Spoon into two pans (9 x 5 x 2-inch).
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and butter over medium heat, bring to slow boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and let melt.
Add quick oats, mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add dry ingredients gradually to creamed mixture. Mix well. Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's, reserving remaining candies for decorating. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet. Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yield: 6 dozen.

title: casserole dish for the microwave
directions: Butter large baking sheet.
In microwave-proof bowl, combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High until mixture bubbles vigorously, about 6 minutes.
Remove mixture from microwave and stir in butter and vanilla.
Return to microwave and cook on High until candy turns light gold color, about 3 minutes. Remove bowl from microwave.
Working quickly, add baking soda to candy mixture and stir briskly (mixture will foam up). Immediately pour out onto prepared baking sheet.
Shake baking sheet from side to side to spread brittle as thinly as possible. Let stand until cold and hard, about 2 hours.
Break brittle into pieces.
Store in airtight container at room temperature for up to 1 month.

title: shrimp mold spread
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add soup and bring to a boil. Cool and add cream cheese and remaining ingredients except shrimp. Chill until slightly thickened; add chopped shrimp and pour into mold. Chill for several hours. Serve as a spread on crackers.

title: colossal cookie
directions: Beat sugar, brown sugar and margarine until creamed well. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients; blend into mixture. Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Place dough in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours or for 45 minutes in freezer until well chilled, but not hard (chilling makes dough less sticky and helps prevent excessive spreading).
Grease a 12-inch round foil or pizza baking pan. Press evenly to within 1 1/2 inches of edge of pan.
May sprinkle additional 1/4 cup chocolate chips on top, pressing into dough slightly for easy handling.
Set pan on cookie sheet.
Bake in center of 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until edges are firm and center has no indentation when lightly touched.
Place on wire rack; cool completely.
When cool, remove from pan and wrap.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove yolks from whites and place in blender with remaining ingredients.
Blend at medium speed until mixture is smooth.
Stop blender and scrap sides occasionally.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg whites.
Garnish with snipped parsley or paprika.
12 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Mix oil, alum, food coloring and boiling water.
Add flour and salt. Mix together.
Knead out lumps when cool enough to handle. Store in covered container.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in baking dish and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in saucepan.
Add bay leaves and water; cover and heat water until it boils.
Turn the heat to low and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients; cover and heat until soup comes to a boil.
Turn the heat to low and cook about 20 minutes or until the vegetables and rice are tender.

title: no-crust cheesecake
directions: Beat together cheese, 2/3 cup of the sugar, eggs and 1/2 teaspoon of the vanilla until smooth.
Pour mixture into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until puffy and brown around edges.
When done, it should spring back when lightly touched in the center.
Cool cheesecake at room temperature 20 minutes.
It will sink slightly during this period.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, baking powder, milk and other ingredients, except flour, and mix. Add flour last. Beat 20 minutes. Bake at 340° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Start in cold oven.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add enough water to make a dough mixture.
Knead on floured surface.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise 1 hour; punch down.
Make rolls.
Place in 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased cake pans.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 40 rolls.

title: easy monkey bread(quick bread)
directions: Combine granulated sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag; set aside.
Combine brown sugar and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn off flame; stir in vanilla.
Set aside.
Place biscuits, a few at a time, in plastic bag.
Shake to coat.
Arrange half biscuits in greased 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Pour half brown sugar mixture over biscuits.
Sprinkle half nuts over brown sugar mixture.
Repeat layers with remaining biscuits, brown sugar mixture and nuts. Bake in 350° gas oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; invert onto serving plate immediately.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients.
In another pot, melt hot cheese, mild cheese and cream, then add vegetables.
Should be thick, so will probably need to add cornstarch and milk mixture.
Next add 3 pounds raw crawfish; cook 20 minutes.
In meantime, boil bag of egg noodles.
When boiled, add to crawfish mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix together the vinegar, sugar and celery seed and bring to a boil. Drain the liquid from the dill pickles. Fill the jar of pickles with water and let stand for 1 hour. Drain and cut the pickles into 1/4-inch slices. Pour the hot liquid over the pickles.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken slowly in oil.
Place in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. To skillet, add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/3 cup water. Season to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Skim off excess fat.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours, basting 3 or 4 times.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: creole style green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Add onions and green pepper to 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Cook until tender. Blend in flour, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add tomatoes and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add the beans and heat.
Top with bacon and serve. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the oven.
Combine everything but broccoli and cheese.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into hot pan.
Bake 50 minutes.
Cool 1 hour before serving.

title: souperburger sandwiches
directions: In medium skillet cook beef and onion until beef is browned, stirring to separate meat. Drain off fat. Add soup, mustard and pepper. Reduce heat to low and simmer. Divide meat mixture among buns. Serve.

title: italian nut balls
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl and blend well. Gradually add flour. Mix well. Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Dip balls halfway into slightly beaten reserved egg whites, then into finely chopped pecans (takes about 3/4 cup of nuts). Place balls on a greased cookie sheet and make a deep hole in the center of each cookie with the handle of a wooden spoon. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until firm to the touch and light brown (do NOT overbake). Immediately remove cookies to cooling racks. While warm, fill centers with a tad of preserves (a red variety). Allow preserves to set before storing cookies. Makes 3 dozen.

title: wild rice and chicken
directions: Cook rice as per directions on the box.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add half and half and chicken broth until thick.
Add chicken and rice.
Spray 2-quart dish with Pam.
Add chicken and rice.
Cook uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: confectioners sugar brownies
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Melt squares of chocolate and add to creamed mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut brownies while hot.

title: gran's cake
directions: Mix all together in mixer bowl about 3 minutes.
Bake in greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients, except pie crust. Cook slowly until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: pineapple cranberry mold
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine reserved juice with pineapple juice (1 3/4 cups) in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Break up cranberry sauce and add to gelatin.
Stir in Port.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened.
Add crushed pineapple and remaining ingredients except for garnish.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate and garnish with sliced pineapple, if desired.

title: sweet tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, bell peppers, onions and hot peppers in heavy pot.
Cover with sugar and vinegar.
Keep alternating with sugar and vinegar until covered.
Cook about 2
hours until tender.
Put up in jars and seal while hot.

title: chicken and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Combine spinach, sour cream, cheese and nutmeg.
Spread mixture over potatoes.
Dip chicken breasts in milk.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Place on top of spinach mixture. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: pinwheels
directions: Spray (2 to 3 short sprays) an 8 to 9-inch pie pan with nonstick spray.
Spread on bottom and sides of pan with paper towel.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pull apart dried beef into pieces.
Mix all ingredients together with hand mixer. Pour into small casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes or until lightly brown and bubbling.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Precook potatoes and onion and drain well.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer potatoes, onions and ground beef.
Top with mushroom soup and repeat layering until all ingredients are layered.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients on lowest speed until dough forms. Shape 1 teaspoon into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375°.

title: cauliflower-broccoli toss
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Wash thoroughly.
Remove stalks from broccoli and wash.
Chop green onions.
Combine cauliflower, broccoli and green onions.
Toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over vegetables, tossing gently.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: chocolate covered balls
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in double boiler.
Remove from heat, stir in sugar.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine buttermilk baking mix, milk and cheese. Mix with a wooden spoon until a soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop dough by heaping tablespoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Combine melted butter or margarine and garlic powder. Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet. Sprinkle biscuits with a little parsley, if desired. Serve warm. Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, onion, salt and Worcestershire.
Beat well. Chill and form into ball.
Roll the ball in chipped beef.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cindy's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except meatballs and cook.
Stir to boiling.
Pour over frozen meatballs in crock-pot.
Cook at high for 1 hour; turn to low until ready to eat.

title: candy coated nuts
directions: Mix together with about 6 tablespoons milk.
Boil slowly without stirring.
Pour over nuts.

title: sole with butter, lemon and parsley(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Put in an ovenproof platter.
Combine the flour and pepper; spread it on wax paper and drag each of the fillets through it so they are well coated.
Shake off excess flour.

title: cornish italiano
directions: Mix dry seasonings and rub hens inside and out.
In large pan, melt butter and oil and brown hens on all sides.
Add wine; cover and simmer until tender (about 45 minutes).
Remove hens to platter; cover and keep warm.
Mix flour with 1/2 cup warm water and add to pan juices for Cornish sauce.
Serve over noodles mixed with sour cream and Parmesan cheese.

title: quick coconutty bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan lined with wax paper; grease wax paper.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Stir in milk.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Put margarine in casserole dish & melt. In the meantime combine sugar & flour into reserve juice. Fold in peaches (or pineapple) & cheese. Spoon mixture into melted margarine. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 min. Serves 6 people.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Add anything else you want, raisins, nuts or coconut.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 8 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients using only enough mayonnaise to hold them together.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients; add eggs and oil, then stir only until moist.
Stir in strawberries.
Spoon into 2 lightly greased 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand to cool before slicing. May be frozen.
Serve as a breakfast bread or dessert after dinner.

title: sparkling limeade
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water and combine with lime juice.
Cool in a 1 1/2-quart pitcher.
Add the sparkling water.
Add crushed ice.
Garnish with a paper thin slice of lime and cherries.

title: tater tot casserole(kid pleaser)
directions: Pat uncooked ground beef into casserole pan.
Sprinkle onion on top of meat.
Pour chicken soup on top of that, then layer Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: biscuit stuffing atop chops
directions: Fry chops.
Place in 9 x 13 greased pan.
Combine all but biscuits in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Cut each biscuit into 10 to 12 pieces.
Stir into soup mixture 1 at a time.
Spoon over chops. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°, checking often so as not to overbake. Recipe over 100 years old.

title: hershey's best brownies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Blend in cocoa.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grandma's baked limas
directions: Wash beans with cold water.
Place beans in kettle and cover with water.
After it comes to a boil, put in a pinch of baking soda.
Parboil until not white, about 10 minutes (being careful that skins of beans don't start coming off).
Drain.
Put beans in roasting pan with ham, salt and pepper, small onion (quartered and sliced), brown sugar and water just to cover beans.
Bake until water cooks down a little at 325°.
Add chili sauce; continue baking until beans are tender and sauce slightly thickened.

title: chipmunk pie
directions: Mix egg and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla, lemon juice, raisins, chopped nuts and diced and peeled apples.
Stir all ingredients until mixed thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tripodi's favorite no bake chewies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in large saucepan and heat until sugar is completely dissolved.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper. Let cool and store or serve.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into ball.
Roll in more pecans and parsley.
Refrigerate overnight.
I get more compliments on this cheese ball than I can count.

title: barbecue style meat loaf
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients well and place in loaf pan. Mix together remaining ingredients; cook until warm and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: orange cranberry muffins
directions: At low speed cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add mandarin orange segments and grated cranberries.
Mix well.
Grease muffin pan well with butter, greasing top surface of pan as well as cups.
Fill muffin cups fairly full.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Serves 12.

title: sour cream pound cake(wedding cake)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Test for doneness.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute in shallow pan, combine the lime juice, oil, chili powder, garlic powder and salt and pepper.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic salt.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook lasagna according to package.
In a greased casserole dish, layer strips of lasagna.
Spread on 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/3 cottage cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat layering process and top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before eating.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine apples, 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Sift flour, 2 cups sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Make a well in center and pour in oil, eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon until well blended.
Spoon 1/3 of batter into a greased 9 or 10-inch angel food pan.
Make a ring of apple mixture, drained, taking care not to have apples touch sides.
Spoon 1/3 batter over.
Make a ring of apples and top with remaining batter.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 375°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Blend peanut butter, butter. Sift in sugar. Shape into balls, 1 inch. Melt chocolate. Dip with toothpick. Place on wax paper and chill.

title: orange brunch
directions: Fix Jell-O like package says.
When partially set, add drained pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Finish setting.
Mix 3 packages of pudding in milk for 2 packages and put on top of set Jell-O.
You can put Cool Whip and crushed pecans on top if you choose.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, dark corn syrup and butter or margarine, melted.
Line pastry shells with pecans. Pour mixture into unbaked shells.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans (9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Make a hole in mixture. Add 2 eggs and 1/2 cup shortening and beat well.
Add a No. 2 can of applesauce and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in large pan (greased), 11 x 13-inch.
Mix and sprinkle over top 1 cup chocolate chips, 1/2 cup nuts and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Combine 1 cup water, vinegar, salt, pepper, 3/4 cup wine and garlic.
Pour over roast and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef across the grain into 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick slanting slices about 3 inches long.
Sprinkle generously with pepper. Melt 1 tablespoon of the butter with oil in a wide frying pan over high heat.
Add beef and cook until just browned on all sides (about 1 1/2 minutes total).
Remove beef and set aside.
Reduce heat to medium.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Separate meat from chili juice with a slotted spoon.
Add Velveeta to hot meat and stir until melted.
Dip each tortilla in hot juice to soften.
Put 1/10th of meat mixture in middle and roll up.
Place seam side down in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Repeat with all tortillas.
Pour remaining chili juice over enchiladas and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash medley
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet until almost crisp.
Add onion, squash and tomatoes; sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring several times. Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Form into cheese ball.

title: peachy cake dessert
directions: Place sliced peaches or pineapple chunks over batter.
Combine the cream cheese, sugar and reserved juice and beat 2 minutes. Spoon to within 1-inch of edge of batter.
Combine the 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350`
for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: apple ring snacks
directions: Spread peanut butter on apple rings.
Sprinkle crumbled granola on peanut butter.
Separate cheese into "strings." Arrange cheese on top of granola.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 8 snacks.

title: apricot-glazed cornish game hens stuffed with wild rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions, omitting flavor packet.
Add tarragon and raisins and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash hens inside and
out; pat dry.
Stuff hens loosely with cooked rice.
Place hens, breast side up, in a large shallow baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: brandy alexander fudge
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with foil and butter.
Combine sugar, butter and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in marshmallow cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into bowl; add almond bark and brandy extract.
Stir well and pour into pan.
To other 1/2 of mixture, add chips and creme de cacao. Blend well and spread over top of white mixture.
Swirl with a knife.
Cool and cut into squares.
Refrigerate until firm.
Lift out by foil.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding together until creamy.
Stir in Cool Whip. Rotate layer of graham crackers and pudding mix until you reach top and then finish with a layer of graham crackers.

title: chicken with a twist
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix chicken and dressing with hot, drained macaroni.
Cool.
Blend mayonnaise and lemon juice with mustard. Stir in last 4 ingredients.
Add to macaroni mixture.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions. Save 1 cup of the batter for the icing. Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13 pan and bake cake as directed.
In a saucepan, melt 1 cup of butter. Add 1 cup sugar and the crushed pineapple with juice. Add the reserved cup of batter and cook until thick. Pour over the cake.

title: baked fillet of sole thermidor
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and dry fish.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and brush on dark side of fillets.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roll up filets with seasoning inside.
Arrange in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour on 1/2 cup of the milk.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions and celery.
Stir in soup and Cheez Whiz.
Boil broccoli and Minute Rice.
Add these to the other mixture.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Stir together.
Pour batter on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until done.
Strain and mix with rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup stuffing on top.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Put butter in cold skillet. Mince garlic, salt, pepper and sugar. Mash together and add to butter. Cook on low heat until butter is melted. Cook meat. Drain, then add to butter mixture. Add tomato sauce and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Cook spaghetti. Put spaghetti in 13 x 9 dish. Add meat mixture on top of spaghetti. Combine cream cheese, sour cream and onions. Add this mixture to top of meat. Add Cheddar cheese on very top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: orange caramel fondue
directions: Microwave caramels, juice and rind in medium bowl on High for 3 minutes. Stir.
Continue cooking 30 seconds to 1 minute or until sauce is smooth, stirring often.
Pour into fondue pot and keep warm while serving.
Dip cake and fruit in sauce and then in coconut and nuts.

title: surprise casserole
directions: Season ground beef with salt and pepper.
Shape into bite-size meatballs around cubes of cheese.
Cook meatballs in skillet until brown on all sides and drain.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Prepare ice ring in advance.
In blender container, combine crushed pineapple and cream of coconut; blend until smooth.
In large punch bowl, combine pineapple mixture, pineapple juice and rum, if desired.
Just before serving, add club soda and ice. Makes 4 quarts.

title: can't fail fudge(five minute fudge)
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in pan over low heat; bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: potato chip cake
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in butter until it resembles crumbs.
Add eggs and sugar and mix well.
Add vanilla and potato chips.
Drop from a teaspoon onto cookie sheet 1/2 inch apart, patting very thin with back of spoon and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Can store in refrigerator for a long period of time.
Spread mixture on bun or thick slices of Italian or French bread.
Add 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of Swiss cheese.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Can freeze, thaw and heat in oven.

title: potato and pork chop casserole
directions: Place thin sliced
raw	potatoes
in
oblong
casserole dish. Sprinkle chopped onions
over potatoes.
Mix 1 can soup with can of water; pour over potatoes.
Place fried pork chops over potatoes.
Spread the other can of soup over top.
Do not dilute soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix together oatmeal, molasses, oil and salt; cover with the boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, 1/2 cup warm water and sugar; add about 6 cups flour.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and put into greased loaf pans.
When double, bake at 375° 40 to 50 minutes.
Coat top of bread with margarine after it comes from the oven for softer crust.

title: presidential popcorn
directions: Put popped popcorn into a large, lightly buttered bowl and keep it warm. In a saucepan, combine sugar, salt, water, corn syrup and vinegar. Bring to a boil. Cook over medium-high heat until the hard-ball stage (250° on a candy thermometer). Stir in vanilla. Slowly pour syrup over popcorn, stirring well. Add jelly beans. Stir well. Turn out onto a lightly buttered (large) tray. Cool. Break up to serve or may be formed into balls, if desired. Makes 5 quarts.

title: microwave turkey divan
directions: Place margarine in medium bowl.
Microwave at High (100%) until melted, 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Blend in flour.
Stir in water, bouillon, cream, sherry and nutmeg.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until thickened, 4 to 7 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin spice dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix baking mix, oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup margarine until crumbly.
Press into rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 10 minutes; cool slightly.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and soda together. Add sugar, ginger and orange rind. Cut butter into mixture. Add potatoes and buttermilk. Add milk slowly and knead
to right consistency. Pat out 1/2-inch thick on cutting board. Cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch circles. Dot with fork. Brush with melted butter. Bake at 400° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: mud hens
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows and nuts on top. Gently press down. Sprinkle on chocolate chips.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine Crisco, peanut butter, brown sugar and 1 cup sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Dough will be stiff.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Take out and press milk chocolate kiss in center of each cookie. Return to oven and bake 3 more minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Then remove to cooling racks.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Beat warm water and egg yolks until creamy.
Cook on medium heat for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice, salt and cayenne pepper.
Beat in butter until smooth.

title: quiche lorraine with swiss cheese
directions: Sprinkle cheese and bacon into pastry-lined pie pan.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over cheese.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 45 minutes or until firm and browned.
(If you insert a clean knife and it comes out clean, quiche is done.) Cut into wedges and serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk and strawberry scones
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and Better 'n Eggs.
Mix until moistened.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead 4 to 5 times.
Pat dough into a 1/2-inch thick circle.
Cut 2-inch circles from dough with biscuit cutter.
Place circles on a baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Place 1 tablespoon of strawberry preserves on top of each and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (reserve some crumbs for top).
Mix pudding and milk, then add ice cream, beating until smooth.
Pour over crust and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Before serving, spread with Cool Whip and top with reserved crumbs.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Blend all ingredients and shape into balls the size of marbles.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crab enchiladas
directions: Combine crab meat, cheese, onion, celery, spices and half of the salsa.
Mix.
Spoon about 1/3 cup down center of tortilla. Roll.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Use all 8 tortillas.
Put remaining salsa on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Use frozen hash browns, thawed.
Mix together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes, mixed with mayonnaise.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: wings
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate for 2 to 3 hours.
Bake 2 to 3 hours, uncovered, basting continuously.
Great for parties.

title: meat loaf barbecue style
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion and beaten egg.
Mix barbecue sauce. Mix about 1/2 barbecue mixture into meat mix.
Shape meat into loaf.
Bake in moderate oven approximately 1 hour.
Baste occasionally with remaining sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, eggs, bread, ketchup, pickles, green pepper and Ragu sauce.
Bake, covered, 1 hour. Remove cover and bake until done.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant meat into small bite size pieces.
Add enough brown gravy to cover; bring to a slow boil.
Stir constantly, adding 2 ounces of salt per hour.
After 9 days and 4 hours, add cut up potatoes and carrots.
Simmer 17 hours longer.
Serves approximately 6,837 guests.
If more stew is needed, the 2 rabbits may be added, but only if necessary since most people don't like finding hare in their stew.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs; mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine remaining 2 eggs and remaining ingredients; beat well.
Spread over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield: about 24.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Place flour in large sealable plastic food bag.
Add beef, half at a time;
shake to coat well.
In 4-quart saucepot heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add onions, bell pepper and garlic;
saute 3 to 4 minutes or until onions are lightly browned. Remover and reserve.
Cook beef half at a time 3 to 4 minutes or until evenly browned on all sides;
remove and reserve.
Stir in paprika;
cook 1 minute.
Add water, bouillon, caraway seed, salt, pepper and cooked vegetables.
Return beef and its juices;
bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with seasonings. Drizzle with melted margarine.
Pour dressing over potatoes.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Optional: Before baking, sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese, bacon bits, or chives.
Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas party mix
directions: Mix oil, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper and garlic powder.
Then pour over the mixture of Corn Chex, Wheat Chex, pretzels, peanuts, pecans and almonds.
Put in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Place in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir several times.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Boil orange rind in 1 cup of water with soda for 4 minutes. Drain and rinse 3 times with fresh water.
Cut or chop rind into very small pieces.
Combine rind with remaining 1/2 cup water and 1 cup sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes; set aside to cool.
Combine remaining 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add pecans.
To the cooled orange mix, add eggs, milk and melted butter.
Combine mixtures and mix well.
Bake in 3 small greased loaf pans at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: santee catfish stew
directions: Fry bacon; take bacon up and fry chopped onions until tender. Drain almost all fat off and put tomato soup, water and ketchup in with onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Return bacon to sauce and let simmer for at least one hour.
About 45 minutes before ready to eat, add serving size pieces of fish.
Do not stir, but poke occasionally.
Serve on hot rice.
Best cooked in a black iron pot.

title: crunchy pea salad(serves 8)
directions: Combine peas, celery, radishes and onions in a medium bowl. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and fold into the vegetables.
Chill overnight, covered.

title: spaghetti sauce(made easy)
directions: Crumble ground beef in large skillet with small amount of grease.
Add chopped onion and cook until meat is browned thoroughly.
Add spaghetti sauce mix (I use the mix with mushrooms), stirring and mixing so mixture won't burn.
Lower heat and add tomato sauce.
Blend thoroughly and simmer 10 minutes on low heat.
Pour over 1 pound of cooked spaghetti and mix.
Do not drain grease from the hamburger.

title: fragrant noodles
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain.
In the same pot, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add green onions and cook 30 seconds. Remove from heat. Stir in drained spaghetti, cilantro, soy sauce and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend
eggs, oil, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, baking powder and
flour.
Then
add apples and pecans.
Bake about 1 hour at 300° in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in a saucepan with butter, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add 3 cups milk; bring to a boil. Stir in cornstarch mixed with a small amount of milk.
Pour into a casserole; top with cheese.
Bake at 350 to 375 degrees until cheese browns.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Let all ingredients come to boil and remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, coconut and peanut butter.
Spoon by tablespoon onto cookie sheet and let cool.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter with onions, salt & pepper. Mix in all other ingredients (we add a little shredded cheese) and spread in greased 9x13 pan.

title: no fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk and cook 12 minutes on medium heat until soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat slightly and pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheese-stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut off about 1/2 inch of the tops.
Remove stems, seeds and white fiber.
Drop into boiling salted water; cook about 5 minutes, or until barely tender.
Drain.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except for the bread crumbs.
Taste to check seasoning; pepper may be needed.
Add the chopped pepper tops.
Fill the peppers with this mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and place in a buttered baking pan.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Beat ingredients and pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: First, cook your meat(s). Add
tomato juice, paste, sugar and vegetables. Depending on how thick or thin you want your soup, you can add more tomato juice or water. Add oil. Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain excess fat.
Sprinkle with soup mix; add water and stir.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl (except chips).
Toss.

title: black beans and rice
directions: In a non-stick skillet, saute onion, peppers, garlic, basil and pepper until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Add beans, rice and vinegar.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: saged fowl in wine sauce
directions: Rub butter on birds.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place birds in large Dutch oven.
Place sage in pot and pour wine into pan until birds are 1/2 covered.
Place lid on pan and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or cook over a regulated open fire until birds are cooked through.
This recipe won first prize at the 1989 Midwest National Rendezvous Cooking Contest.

title: fruit filled thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, egg yolks, salt and vanilla.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with fork until foamy.
Dip each ball into whites; roll in nuts.

title: holy smokes
directions: Mix together flour, butter and nuts.
Press into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: harding dish
directions: Fry hamburg, onion and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the rest in order given.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: taco pie casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Doritos and cheese in casserole dish.
Add Doritos.
Top with cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbles appear, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt; gradually stir in scalded milk.
Pour filling into pie shell, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with knife 2 inches from edge of crust.
Cool and chill.

title: apple crisps
directions: Make dough with flour, shortening and milk.
Refrigerate to chill.
Heat sugar, margarine, vanilla and water until mixture boils; pour into large baking dish.
Roll out dough on floured surface; sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Place apples on dough; roll up like jelly roll.
Slice and place in hot liquid. Bake in a 300° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, or until apples are tender and crust is brown.

title: chuck wagon carrots
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, place carrots.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to a full boil.
Cook over medium heat until carrots are crisp but tender (8 to 12 minutes).
Drain; return to pan and add remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
In another pan, melt Velveeta (spray pan with Pam first).
Mix broccoli and cheese together and pour into glass pie plate or casserole dish.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two deep pie crusts. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: rich brown steak dinner
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper; roll in flour.
Cook onions in hot shortening until tender, but not brown.
Remove onions and brown meat slowly on both sides.
Place meat in a 3-quart casserole.
Add onions, potatoes and bay leaf.
Pour soup on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Add frozen green beans and bake 15 minutes more.

title: terrific turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a loaf.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Use a meat thermometer (170°) to be sure of doneness.
Don't overcook.
Serve with mashed potatoes and gravy. Serves 4.

title: chili(made easy)
directions: In large skillet, cook meat until almost browned.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Continue cooking.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant tava
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ground meat with 1/2 cup of the juice from the tomatoes and 2 teaspoons of the tomato paste.
Add onion, green pepper, allspice, pepper, salt and garlic.
Mix well and set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Form cheese ball and roll it in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: liver with onions
directions: Saute onions in butter and sage in a large skillet for about 10 minutes. Shake liver in bag of seasoned flour. Add liver to onions and cook until done, stirring frequently.

title: 7-layer cookies for christmas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put cracker crumbs in bottom.
Drizzle melted margarine over crumbs.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, walnuts and coconut on top.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes(4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tops off tomatoes; remove the center pulp.
Set tomato shells aside.
Chop the center pulp and set aside, discarding excess juice.
In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add onion and garlic and saute just until softened.
Add tomato pulp, anchovies, parsley, bread crumbs, wine, remaining olive oil, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Spray 6 x 10-inch baking dish with canola oil.
Spread evenly in dish and bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Use Reddi-Wip for topping.
Enjoy.

title: pot roast with sauerkraut and carrots(395 calories per serving)
directions: About 3 1/4 hours before serving:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim any excess fat from bottom round roast.
In covered 8-inch Dutch oven, bake meat, onion, bay leaf, salt, pepper and 1 cup of water for 2 1/2 hours.
Add sauerkraut and carrots to meat in Dutch oven.
Cover and bake 40 minutes longer or until carrots and meat are tender.
Place meat on warm platter and surround with vegetables.
Makes 10 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: If raisins are used, put in saucepan with enough water to cover and bring to boil.
Drain thoroughly.
Place beaten eggs and sugar in a large bowl and mix.
Then add oil; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and zucchini.
Then add dry ingredients.
Bake in 2 regular size loaf pans at 375° for 1 hour or until bread shrinks from side of pan.

title: confetti pizza bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, mashed potatoes and eggs.
Add cocoa, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder.
Mix in milk and flour.
Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: curry glaze(double for large amounts of chicken)
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, then simmer, uncovered, stirring often, about 15 minutes or until thickened.

title: lucy's magic quiche
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add half and half, eggs, ham and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crisp honey cookies
directions: Cream butter and honey. Sift together flour, soda and spices. Mix in wheat germ. Combine dry ingredients with creamed mixture. Chill 1 hour. Roll on floured board about 1/8 inch thick. Cut out with cookie cutter. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on rack and spread with frosting.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and flavored yogurt in an electric mixer until well blended. Pour mixture, divided equally, into both 9-inch pie shells. Garnish with fresh fruit or nuts.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours. Serve frozen.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Puree in food processor.
Place in baking pan.
Warm in oven until juice separates from cheese at side of dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with fresh French bread pieces.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello powder with cottage cheese.
Then mix drained, crushed pineapple and oranges together.
Add to jello and cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve on a bed of lettuce if desired.

title: linda's salad
directions: Heat pineapple in saucepan (juice and fruit).
To this, add jello;
stir
and
mix well.
Cool.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.

title: sausage bites
directions: Combine and shape into 1 1/4-inch size balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lentil soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large saucepan.
Add water and chicken broth.
(May need to add more water or broth to cover vegetables.)
Bring to the boil and simmer 25 to 45 minutes or until vegetables and beans are tender.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place ingredients in pan in layers as listed.
Pour cold water slowly.
Melt the margarine and dribble over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cake is good warm or cold.
May serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: gulyas (hungarian goulash)
directions: Saute bacon; remove from pan.
Saute onion in bacon grease; remove.
Brown beef.
Return bacon and onion to pot.
Add seasonings, broth, wine and green pepper.
Bring to a boil; simmer, covered, 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cook 30 minutes more. You may thicken the juices, if preferred, before serving.

title: date drop cookies
directions: Combine dates and water; bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes; cool.
Set aside 2 tablespoons date mixture for frosting.
Beat in egg, sugar and buttermilk.
Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: puppy chow snack(for humans)
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and oleo or butter.
Drizzle over the Wheat Chex in a large bowl; mix, then add powdered sugar, added slowly and shake to coat.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop in greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be kept in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done; remove from bone.
Heat soups, broth and tomatoes in saucepan.
Place in baking dish in layers the chicken, onion, Doritos chips and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over layered chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin honey chews
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, honey, egg and peel.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and oats; beat well.
Add raisins.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake about oven center at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until evenly browned.
Let stand on sheet 2 to 3 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir together noodles, mushrooms, chicken and soup.
Put in baking dish.
Slice butter across top of mixture.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese across top of dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Double recipe for 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: carolina chew cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs, beating well.
Blend in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Spoon batter into well-greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar, then cut into squares.
Cookies will fall as they cool.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and saute green onions.
Add soup, salt, sour cream and cheese.
Using 3-quart Pyrex pan, layer potatoes in pan evenly.
Gently stir in sauteed mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and mix in cornflake crumbs.
Pour over top of casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Chill for 10 minutes.
Roll and cut out. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: apple-cheese custard
directions: Spread apple slices in a well buttered 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (about 2-inches deep).
In blender or food processor, combine cottage cheese, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, eggs and half and half. Whirl or process until smooth.
Pour mixture evenly over apples. Split cardamon pods, removing seeds (you should have about 1/2 teaspoon).
Discard pods. Sprinkle seeds evenly over apple mixture.
Bake custard at 350° for about 1 hour until apples are tender and top is golden brown.
Serve warm or at room temperature with whipped cream, if you wish.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Brew 1-quart tea for 3 to 5 minutes, according to desired strength.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Combine the rest of the ingredients
to the tea and simmer.

title: golden mushroom stew
directions: Place all ingredients, except cornstarch, in Dutch oven or stockpot.
Cook on medium until boils.
Turn to low and simmer for at least 1/2 hour.
Add cornstarch while stirring.
Stew will thicken and be ready to serve.
You may need to add water throughout cooking time.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour in baking dish. Cover with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in blender until real fine.
Place half into the bottom of an 8-inch flower pot.
Save rest for top of dessert. Use mixer to blend Cool Whip, cream cheese, 10x sugar and butter. In another bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Combine with cream cheese mixture and pour over crushed Oreos.
Refrigerate until serving time, then sprinkle the remaining Oreos on top.
Decorate with artificial plastic flower and gummy worms on top.
Serve with garden trowel.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in mixture of egg and milk. Then roll in bread crumbs.
Place chicken into oiled baking pan, skin side up.
Make sure pieces are not touching.
Dot with butter or margarine and bake 45 minutes at 350° until nicely browned.
Do not turn.
Drain fat.
Pour Marsala wine over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: layered pudding delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with graham crackers.
(Break crackers if necessary.)
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Let stand 5 minutes, then blend in whipped topping.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, then add milk and cream cheese and heat and stir until well blended.
Add other ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve from chafing dish with Melba toast rounds.

title: hamburg loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Turn into a loaf pan. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nutty macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine egg whites and salt in a large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed until foamy. Add sugar gradually, beating at high speed until very stiff peaks form. Blend in vanilla. Fold in coconut and pecans gently.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets lined with baking parchment.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown. Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt 1/2 cup peanut butter in chocolate bar.
Put chocolate in muffin pans; let set 20 to 30 minutes.
Melt remaining peanut butter, then put on top of chocolate.
Let cool.

title: hawaiian brownies
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place breast halves between waxed paper and pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer onto warm serving platter.
Add green onions, lemon-lime juice, parsley, brandy and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 minutes, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth; whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over All-Bran.
Let stand until cool.
Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with 1 3/4 cups buttermilk.
Add the bran mix, then add 2 more cups dry All-Bran. Mix well.
Cover.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Do not stir!
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Mixture will keep 5 weeks.
Makes 1/2 gallon.
May add nuts, raisins and currants.

title: fairy food
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and vinegar in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook to a hard-crack stage (300°).
Turn off heat and add soda, mixing quickly.
Pour immediately into a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Cool, then invert on a tray.
Spread with melted chocolate. Break into chunks.
Yields about 1 pound.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Boil chicken whole in 3 quarts of water with bouillon cubes. Mix all other ingredients together with enough stock to form into biscuit shaped patties.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until solid and brown.
Remove whole chicken from pot and place in oven to brown.
Place baked stuffing patties in pot of broth where chicken was cooked.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until softened slightly.
Chicken may be sliced and served with stuffing as a side dish or combined in broth.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Season with salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients. Cook on low in slow cooker all day.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix together well.
Make log and roll in a mixture of 1 1/2 tablespoons chili powder and 1 1/2 tablespoons paprika.

title: fruit and pudding crisp
directions: Combine fruit, 1 tablespoon pudding mix, brown sugar and fruit syrup. Put in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole or 8-inch square baking pan.
Set aside.

title: carrot nut bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
In a large bowl, put oil, carrots, eggs, water and dates.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts last.
Grease 2 loaf pans and bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.
This bread is very moist and freezes well.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling, salted water according to package directions. Drain well. Cook onion and green pepper in diet margarine until tender. Stir in condensed soup, mushrooms, pimiento, skim milk and basil. Lay half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish. Top with half the chicken, cheeses, and soup mixture. Repeat the process. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with remaining American and Parmesan cheese. Bake two minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: brown butter frosting
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook and stir butter over medium heat for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Pour into a mixing bowl. Add 3 cups confectioners sugar and orange juice. Beat until smooth. Add enough of the remaining sugar to reach spreading consistency. Spread frosting between filled cakes; frost top and sides of cake. Sprinkle with nuts. Store in the refrigerator. Yield: 12 servings.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine and pour into Pam-sprayed casserole.

title: souper wieners
directions: Heat wieners, vegetables (with liquid) and soup.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.
(Six cups cooked rice.)

title: grandma rudolph's tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to mixture.
Blend dry ingredients.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch and cut in desired shapes and sizes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Three or four days ahead, with an electric mixer thoroughly combine Cheddar, cream cheese, garlic powder, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into 2 thin logs.
On a wax paper, sprinkle chili powder.
Roll cheese logs until thoroughly coated with chili powder.
Wrap logs in wax paper, Saran Wrap or foil. Refrigerate 3 to 4 days to ripen.
To serve, arrange logs on board, slicing some with assorted crackers nearby.
Let guests help themselves.
Leftovers keep well.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: avocado vinaigrette
directions: In covered container, shake oil, vinegar, parsley, salt, pepper and sugar.
Halve avocados lengthwise; twist each half in opposite directions to separate.
Remove pit.
Drizzle dressing over halves in serving dishes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cashew candy(you can't eat just one!)
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add sugar, syrup and water.
Heat, stirring constantly to crack stage (300°).
Watch carefully after 280°.
Stir in coarse nuts right at 300°.
Pour immediately into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scrape pan quickly and spread evenly in pan.
Cool.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Spread on cake and cool.
Cover and store in refrigerator (enhances taste).

title: baked beans
directions: Boil navy beans, soda and water to cover until tender.
Pour off water.
Put in baking pot or crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Bake until tender and golden brown.

title: salmon stew
directions: In a saucepan, pour salmon and liquid in pan. Remove black skin and bones. Add milk and butter. Heat on medium until just before boiling point. Serve with crackers and sprinkle top with grated cheese.

title: boneless chicken breasts
directions: Cut chicken (skinless) to 1 to 1 1/2-inch wide; leave the length.
Shake chicken in flour.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour soy sauce and orange juice on dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cut with a fork!

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Mix in soup mixture.
Add 1 cup of the noodles.
Add meat, cashews and salt.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Sprinkle a little garlic powder on beef.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the bouillon and let simmer until meat is tender, about an hour.
Add onion and mushrooms and cook about 10 minutes.
Add about a teaspoon of flour to remaining bouillon and stir
well.
Mix with meat mixture.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup sour cream.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Mix all together except tortillas.
Place layer of tortillas on bottom of baking dish.
Alternate chicken mixture and cheese. Finish tortillas and chicken on top.
Cover and bake 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate coating
directions: Melt in double boiler and coat candy, pretzels, etc.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add all other ingredients, except chips.
Beat for a few minutes.
Add 3/4 of chips and mix.
Pour into floured and greased tube pan.
Sprinkle rest of chips on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: diet cheese danish
directions: Mix and spread on toast; put under broiler until bubbly.

title: buffalo bill's wings
directions: Cut wing tips off at joint and discard; cut each wing in half at joint.
On rack in broiler pan, arrange wings.
Broil 6 inches from heat 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear, turning occasionally.

title: ms. jane's vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a cookie sheet and cook according to to instructions.
Combine dressing mix, cream cheese, and Miracle Whip.
Spread mixture onto cooked crescent rolls.
Top with vegetables and cheese.

title: blueberry lemon muffins
directions: Sift together flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Make well in center of mixture.	Combine milk, egg and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly, just until moistened.
Toss together blueberries and 2 tablespoons sugar. Gently stir into batter with lemon peel.
Fill greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pans, 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
While muffins are still warm, dip tops in melted butter or margarine, and then in a little granulated sugar.

title: sherry's party dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite-size cuts.
Add all the ingredients in pot or crock-pot.
Simmer on low until dogs are done.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 people.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain juice from first 3 ingredients.
Put in casserole and add pork and beans.
Dice bacon and fry crisp.
Do not drain grease.
Add onion, dry mustard, vinegar and brown sugar. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over beans; stir and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with hand mixer until smooth.
Serve with apples and/or popcorn.

title: fruit delight
directions: Prepare ahead of time to allow flavors to develop.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Saute beef, onion, celery, green pepper.
Add to remaining ingredients in a 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (or microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes) until heated through. Makes 8 servings, approximately 300 calories each.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan 1/2 full of lettuce (torn or sliced).
Add layers of celery, green onions, green peppers and green peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; spread over peas. Sprinkle with sugar and crumbled bacon.
Cover with cheese and refrigerate overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Shape into a loaf and put in a deep dish.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Beat together in blender while pouring salad oil and olive oil slowly.
Serve with fresh spinach, leaf lettuce or raw cauliflower.
Top salad with shredded Muenster cheese.
Yields 2 1/2 pints.

title: dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of an 8x8 inch microwave-safe dish. Sprinkle onions over cream cheese.
Heat chili and pour over onions/cream cheese. Sprinkle cheese over top. Microwave on high about 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
This can be heated in an oven at 350 degrees for about 10 minutes. Serve hot with corn or nacho chips.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in Dutch oven or large casserole dish. Cover and bake as follows: 250° for 5 hours or 300° for 4 hours or 325° for 3 hours.

title: crab salad
directions: Wash lettuce.
Tear or chop into bowl.
Add rest of the ingredients; mix.

title: cucumber-tuna boats
directions: Cut cukes in half lengthwise; scrape out seeds.
Cut a thin slice from bottom so they will set flat.
Sprinkle cavity with salt.
Combine remaining ingredients and fill shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: mom's crock-pot potatoes
directions: Drain new potatoes. Melt butter and add sour cream, chives, salt and pepper.
This will make the "sauce".

title: nothing cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and pineapple (do not drain). Add vanilla, mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: evelyn barrett's mustard sauce
directions: Cook in double boiler.
Simmer 3 hours.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: cherry mess
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cherries, then pineapple in bottom of pan.
Pour dry cake mix over pineapple.
Cut up butter and place on top of cake mix.
Cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.

title: tina's crackers
directions: Place dressing mix, oil and peppers in a large sealable bowl (or large zippered bag) and mix well.
Add crackers and toss gently.
Let sit, tossing occasionally.

title: seven day coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix by directions on box, dividing into 3 layers. The day before making cake, mix together the coconut, sour cream and sugar.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
When cake is cool, put mixture on each layer.
Cover cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Cover cake and place in refrigerator for 7 days.

title: strawberry ice cream punch
directions: Mix juices, strawberries and 7-Up together into a chilled punch bowl.
Stir gently.
Spoon ice cream to float on top.

title: wild rice potato soup
directions: Saute onion with butter until golden brown.
Add cream of chicken and potato soup with milk, basil, thyme, salt, pepper, fried bacon and rice.
Heat on medium heat until milk starts to form little bubbles around the pan and milk has risen about 1/4 inch.
Pour into bowls and sprinkle cheese on it and parsley. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: meat cups
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Drain fat.
Add barbecue sauce. Simmer 10 minutes.
Separate biscuits.
Roll each one into a 6-inch circle.
Put each into a greased muffin tin, forming a cup. Fill with beef mixture.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400° until biscuits are slightly browned.

title: three "c" bread
directions: Combine beaten eggs, oil and milk.
In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add egg mixture, mix until thoroughly combined.
Stir in carrot, coconut, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Turn into 4 well-greased and floured (16 ounces) fruit or vegetable cans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from cans and cool thoroughly.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight or until used.
To make one large loaf, bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix well and pour over ice.
Serve.

title: baked french toast
directions: Place bread slices in layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat remaining ingredients (except confectioners sugar) until completely blended and granulated sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture over bread; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 48 hours.
Bread will soak up liquid.
When ready to serve, heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan.
Use a wide spatula to transfer slices to pan.
Allow space between each piece.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until puffed and lightly browned. Dust with confectioners sugar and garnish with sliced fresh berries.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven-fried cauliflower
