directions: Place mayonnaise in a large heavy-duty Zip-top plastic bag. Add cauliflower, seal and shake to coat. Place breadcrumbs in a large heavy-duty Zip-top plastic bag. Add half of cauliflower mixture. Seal and shake to coat. Spread in a single layer onto a lightly greased baking sheet. Repeat with remaining cauliflower mixture and breadcrumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 8 servings.

title: potatoes a la harriet
directions: Parboil the potatoes.
Let potatoes become cold and then grate in casserole dish.
Pour in whipping cream and add butter, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are done. Best when potatoes are not too soft.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream chicken bake
directions: Combine flour, salt, paprika, Accent and pepper in paper bag and shake chicken in the bag.
Brown slowly in oil.
Pour off excess fat.
Surround chicken with potatoes.
Top with onions. Pour soup over chicken and potatoes.
When potatoes are done, pour sour cream over all.
Cook 5 minutes more.

title: hobo stew
directions: Chop onion, slice carrots and choplets.
Saute onion and carrots.
Add water and cook until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch and add choplets.
Heat through and pour over hot rice.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until butter melts.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Skin chicken and arrange in sprayed casserole or baking pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Chip the dried beef and put on top of chicken.
Combine soups and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken and beef.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms and peas.
Combine ingredients.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with onion rings.

title: crab quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust in pie plate or quiche pan if you have one.
In a bowl, beat eggs until blended.
Stir in cream, onion, salt and red pepper.
Pat crabmeat dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle crabmeat and cheese in pastry-lined pan.
Pour egg mixture over crabmeat and cheese; sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Let quiche stand 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sure and easy fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over slow boiling water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread candy onto buttered platter.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: myrt's banana pudding
directions: Prepare puddings according to package directions.
Mix together sour cream and Cool Whip.
Combine sour cream/Cool Whip mixture and puddings.
Alternate layers of wafers, pudding mixture and bananas in a bowl.
Decorate edges of bowl with wafers, letting final round of wafers extend above top of bowl.
(A small dab of pudding on back of wafers will make wafers stick to bowl.)

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cut up into small pieces. Mix together the soups and salad dressings. Put a layer of chicken in dish, then a layer of mixture, a layer of cheese and chow mein noodles. Continue layers until dish is full. Can top with slivered almonds. Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water; remove and debone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and mushroom juice.
Drain.
Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces and spaghetti in 3-inch pieces.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Pour fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Crust will rise to top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, until crust is golden brown.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Grate
cheese.	Soften margarine.
Combine all.
Refrigerate. Roll
into	balls.	Mash
down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
If you don't chill this, can be pushed through a cookie press.

title: orange julius(child's recipe)
directions: Put in blender for 30 seconds.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix, using electric mixer 2 eggs, cream cheese and confectioners sugar (save a little sugar to sprinkle on top of baked cake).
Spread this mixture on top of first layer.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares or bars.

title: betty's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients and stir as mixture comes to a boil.
Turn heat down; simmer for 1 hour.

title: pickled okra
directions: You will need boiled jars and lids.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook Creamettes; drain.
Add cubed corned beef and cheese. Mix milk with chicken soup and add.
Add onion.
Put into casserole; sprinkle buttered crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade orange refresher
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a blender container and process at high speed.
Add ice cubes, a few at a time, blending until slushy.
Garnish with orange slices and mint, if desired. Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: ham and spaghetti casserole(silver bowl winner 1980)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Mix spaghetti, ham, sour cream, soup, mushrooms, reserved mushroom liquid, olives, onion, seasoned salt, mustard, and worcestershire sauce.
Pour into ungreased baking dish, 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4 inches.
Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Mix 1/2 cup cheese and buttered bread crumbs; sprinkle in diagonal rows over casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese between rows.
Bake until casserole begins to bubble, about 30 minutes.
8 servings.

title: buttermilk spice cake
directions: Pour buttermilk and hot water over orange rind or dates and raisins if used; let stand while assembling other ingredients. Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and spices.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Turn batter into greased and lightly floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly; while still warm, spoon Broiled-On Frosting on top.
Place under broiler until frosting bubbles and browns lightly.
Serves 6.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Blend well.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream. Place in oblong Pyrex casserole and freeze until ready to serve. Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving for easier cutting.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream together butter, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and milk alternately, starting and ending with flour.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Sprinkle in baking powder and mix.
Lightly grease and flour tube pan.
Pour mixture in.
Put in cold oven.
Set temperature for 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apricot pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple
and
gelatin in small saucepan; heat until gelatin
is
dissolved.
Remove
from
heat.
Add sugar, baby food and cream cheese; mix well.
Do not overbeat.
Chill slightly. Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into an 8-inch pan. Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: sourdough white bread
directions: Rinse large bowl in hot water.
Put 1 cup warm water in bowl and sprinkle with yeast.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Add flour and mix thoroughly with hands.
Cover and let set for 1 hour or until double its bulk.
Turn out on heavily floured surface and knead for 10 minutes.
Place in 2 round pans, well-greased with oil.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Slit with razor and let rise for 40 minutes.
Brush with eggs and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: sugar-free grape sherbet
directions: Heat 1 cup thawed concentrate to boiling; dissolve gelatin in this.
Cool completely.
Combine remaining concentrate, milk and gelatin mixture in large mixing bowl; stir until well blended. Pour into freezer can of ice cream freezer and churn according to manufacturer's directions.
Remove from can and pack into plastic container with tight fitting lid.
Ripen several hours or overnight in freezer.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together beans, soup and enough milk to make a little "gravy" on the beans.
Pour into a baking dish and top with the onion rings.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour, or until onion rings are brown.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Beat first four ingredients at medium speed until creamed. Add eggs.
Combine the next ingredients, then mix into creamed mixture.
Drop by tablespoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
One baking sheet at a time, bake 7 to 9 minutes until cookies are set.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overbake!
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Place sheets of foil on countertop.
Remove cookies on foil to cool completely.
Yields about 3 dozen cookies.
Bake at 375°.

title: christmas goodies
directions: Melt chocolate in double broiler.
Mix with pretzels and peanuts and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add tomato soup and green beans.
Pour into casserole and top with whipped potatoes and grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir together dry ingredients; set aside.
In small bowl mix egg, banana, milk and oil.
Add liquid mixture, all at once, to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cup 2/3 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: baked apple with sauce
directions: Wash and core six large apples.
Fill the centers with sugar and cinnamon.
Pour a little water over the apples.
Bake in moderate oven.
Make a sauce with sugar, cornstarch and one egg. Flavor with vanilla.
Children like them.

title: louisiana style lit'l smokies
directions: Fry bacon over medium heat until crisp and brown.
Add onion and green peppers and cook until tender.
Stir in pineapple juice, ketchup and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Add Lit'l Smokies, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or put in crock-pot on low to keep warm.

title: tangy buffet meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape to form 1-inch balls.
Bake in shallow baking pan at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding mix into Cool Whip; add pineapple, marshmallows and walnuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in mold and refrigerate (or freeze).
Makes 9 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft. Add sugar and peanut butter. Fold in Cool Whip. Put in shell and chill.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in baking dish with chicken on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
More liquid may be needed.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Using an electric knife, slice angel food cake into 3 equal layers.
Mix instant pie filling
according to package directions. Fold together Cool Whip, drained pineapple and instant pie filling.
Place bottom layer on serving plate.
Spread evenly with Cool Whip mixture, then place 4 to 6 cherries evenly around the bottom layer.
Add middle layer and the top layer, repeating process.
After all 3 layers are assembled, drizzle remaining Cool Whip mixture so that it runs down the sides and middle.
Drizzle remaining cherries on top of top layer of Cool Whip mixture.

title: best and easiest chocolate pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in water and milk.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Mix rice, all soups and water together.
Lay chicken on top. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in covered dish.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone it.
Add chicken to baking dish.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Stir well.
Add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add layers
in above order.
Pour milk over all.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 40 (1 x 2-inch) squares.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine water, whole cloves and sugar and bring to a boil. Boil about 20 minutes.
Lower heat and add tea, pineapple juice, orange juice and water.
Heat until desired temperature.

title: impossible pie(custard)
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend for 1 minute.
Pour into 10-inch greased pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool and crumble.
Layer the ingredients until all are used.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Stir well and pour in 9 x 12-inch greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 13 X 9 inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix coconut and pecans and place in prepared pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, adding vanilla.
Pour cake mix over coconut-pecan mixture.
Melt butter and cream cheese over low heat in saucepan.
When melted, stir in powdered sugar. Spoon over top of cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before turning out of pan.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and soda.
Add beaten eggs, fruit cocktail and nuts.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares and pour on topping while warm.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Mix sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake until brown, 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars, about 1 1/2 x 2-inches.

title: golden puffs
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add oil, milk and egg. Stir with fork until thoroughly mixed; drop from teaspoon into deep hot Wesson oil or fat.
Fry until golden brown (about 3 minutes). Drain on absorbent paper.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture or glaze puffs by dipping into thin confectioners sugar icing with a few drops of lemon juice added.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Continue beating. Add 1 egg at a time.
Put 1 vanilla wafer (salerno) per 2-inch foil baking cup.
Pour 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Makes approximately 36.
Spoon fruit pie filling on top and serve.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, juices and salt.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add pineapple, celery, apples and nuts.
Fold in the cream which has been whipped.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Freeze.
Cut into squares.
Serve frozen on lettuce leaf.

title: date pineapple bars
directions: Grease a 7 x 11-inch cake pan.
Preheat oven to moderate 350°. Cream butter or margarine with brown sugar and eggs at high speed of electric mixer, guiding mixture into beaters with rubber scraper, until light and creamy.
Sift flour; measure and sift with baking powder, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with honey to the creamed mixture. Stir in crushed pineapple, chopped dates and walnuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
When cool decorate with a thin sugar icing made by adding one tablespoon boiling water to 1 cup sifted confectioners sugar.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: pecan sandies cookies
directions: Cream butter/margarine, water, vanilla and sugar.
Then add flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven, 325°, about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and then roll in confectioners sugar.
Finish cooling.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix avocado with guacamole dip mix.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan hamburger, avocado mix, lettuce, tomatoes, onions, taco sauce and sour cream.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Do not mix.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cracker mix
directions: Stir ingredients well and pour over crackers.
Stir occasionally.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour on top crust.
Bake at 350° for 25	minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle
on
some powdered sugar and smear. Refrigerate when fully cooled.
Cut into squares.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to sugar-egg mixture.
Makes stiff dough. Roll and cut size of plate.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool and spread with apples.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Add other ingredients, except cheese and crumbs.
Add cheese and crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Core apples, leaving bottom intact to allow apple to hold filling.
Enlarge hole with knife to make a space about 2-inches deep and 2-inches across.
Saute onions, celery, chopped apple and sausage until meat is thoroughly cooked. Add raisins and 1/2 cup apple concentrate, bring to a boil.
Cook over high heat until liquid thickens a bit (about 1 minute). Divide filling among apples and place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch or larger baking dish.
Mix remaining concentrate with 1/2 cup water and pour in bottom of dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting often.
Serve warm.
Good for brunch.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Beat egg white with fork until it foams a little.
Add vanilla; beat a little.
Gradually add sugar and flour.
Add pecans, a few at a time.
Coat with mixture. Drop on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes. Let cool some before removing from cookie sheet.

title: grandma's soft molasses bars
directions: Put eggs, spices, salt and sugar together and beat.
Add shortening and mix.
Add molasses; mix.
Add flour last with soda and boiling water.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: annie's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as directed on box for 5 minutes; drain. Combine beaten eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise; fold into broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Pat dry.
Prick each potato with a fork in a few places.
Bake potatoes on a rack at 400° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are cooked.
Cut a thin slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out the pulp into a bowl.
Mash the potato pulp with the hot soy milk until fluffy.
Beat in soy margarine and scallions.
Add seasoning.
Add TVP based bacon bits into potato mixture.
Spoon potato mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Place potatoes on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are piping hot and cheese is melted, about 15 minutes. Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: surprise cornbread
directions: Blend in large bowl.
Pour into greased long pan.
Bake until golden brown at 400°, about 45 minutes.

title: mama's coconut or banana cream pie
directions: Add first 5 ingredients together in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat.
Bring to a boil.
When thickened, add coconut or bananas and vanilla.
Cook and pour into pie crust.
Use egg whites to make meringue.

title: chicken breast fillets with scallions and cream
directions: Dredge chicken in flour mixture and shake off excess.
Melt butter in a skillet over medium-high heat.
Add breast halves, 3 at a time, and fry quickly until golden on both sides.
Remove to a serving platter.
(The centers should not be cooked through.) Add a bit more butter (if desired) and the scallions to the pan and saute for 1 minute.
Add cream and boil until reduced to a sauce-like consistency.
Return breasts to pan to heat through and finish cooking in the center (2 minutes, roughly).
When the centers are just barely done, remove chicken to a serving platter, pour on sauce and serve.
Serves 4.

title: velvet hot chocolate
directions: Place chocolate in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts.
Set aside. Combine milk, half and half and sugar in a saucepan.
Scald mixture over medium heat.
Gradually add 1 cup milk mixture to melted chocolate, stirring until smooth.
Add chocolate mixture to remaining milk mixture.
Stir in rum and amaretto.
Top each serving with whipped cream and garnish with a cinnamon stick. Serve immediately.
Serves 5 cups.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind and mix.
Boil 30 minutes.
Sterilize jars and seal.

title: swiss steak
directions: Rub flour on meat.
Brown slowly in hot oil in heavy skillet. Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook over low heat or in oven at 325° about 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Add a small amount of boiling water, if necessary, for gravy, if desired.

title: southern pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take casserole and put the oleo in it; melt in oven as it preheats.
Mix sugar with flour and baking powder.
Add milk; stir real good (thin batter).
Pour into casserole.
Open can or package of fruit; pour contents into the center of batter.
Do not stir!
Put in oven.
Cake will come to the top.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Garnish with hard sauce (oleo mixed with confectioners sugar).
Serves 6.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage until pink is gone (not hard).
Fry onion, celery and pepper until tender.
Let water boil.
Add soup mix; stir. Add rice and stir.
Combine all ingredients together.
Bake in covered dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dump into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Turn oven to 325° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Use an electric mixer to mix the butter, brown sugar, flour, eggs, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Then by hand, mix the chocolate chips in.
Heat for 7 minutes at the temperature of 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles(makes about 10 cups)
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Put remaining ingredients into saucepan and boil until the sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over cucumber mixture. Fill into jars with lids.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps up to 1 year.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Mix well.
Chill until set.

title: make play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put mixture into a boiler.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture forms a doughy lump, pour on waxed paper.
Knead until smooth.
Store in airtight container.

title: foil baked roast beef
directions: Measure liquid and
add
water	if
necessary to make 4 tablespoons.
Place roast
on large, heavy piece of foil.
Mix the onion and mushroom soups together and
sprinkle
over
the top of the roast (no other seasoning
is
necessary).
Dribble the
water or
mushrooms and liquid over the	soup
and
seal tightly in foil.
Place on a cookie sheet and	bake
in a 250° oven for at least 5 hours.
Don't try to hurry it.
(Very good for inexpensive meats.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Rub meat with flour.
Brown in butter mixture.
Add water and simmer for 15 minutes in covered pan.
Add soups and mushrooms.
Simmer 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: danish kringle
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Work flour, sugar, salt and lard like pie crust.
Beat egg yolks and milk together.
Pour yeast mixture into milk mixture and beat well.
Cover and chill overnight or at least 3 hours.
Divide dough into 4 pieces.
Roll out each piece of dough to about 1/4-inch.
Spread with the 3 egg whites. Sprinkle with brown sugar and spread with your favorite filling (preserves, jam, jelly or nut).
Fold each piece into thirds (sort of fold over).
Let rise while oven is heated at 325°.
Use greased cookie sheets.
Bake 30 minutes.
Ice when hot.
Makes 4 Kringles.

title: chicken cilantro
directions: Cook and
stir onion and garlic in margarine and oil in large skillet
until
onion is tender.
Add chicken, salt and pepper. Cook and stir over medium high heat until done, about 10
minutes. Stir
in cilantro.
Pour pan juices over chicken to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, water and Karo; cook to soft ball stage (240° to 245°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and peanut butter. Using mixer, beat until thick and no longer shiny.

title: mandel bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in order listed together.
Spread on greased and Pam'd cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Take out and slice while warm; separate half onto another cookie sheet and put back in oven for 10 minutes.

title: baked cornflake chicken
directions: Combine cornflake crumbs and seasonings in shallow bowl. Soak chicken in milk then dredge chicken in crumb mixture. Place on baking pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and no longer pink.

title: snapper with tarragon-lime mayonnaise
directions: Rinse fillets with cold water and pat dry.
Arrange in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, coated with vegetable cooking spray.

title: baptist roast
directions: Place roast in large ceramic oven dish that can be covered. Top with seasonings.
Wash potatoes, cut in half lengthwise and place around roast, cut side up.
Clean carrots, cut in half lengthwise and place around roast and potatoes.
Add water.
Cover and place in 250° oven for 3 to 4 hours.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Just before serving, pour the Catalina dressing and toss lightly.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing at least 2 hours or overnight. (Do not add water.
Do not cover so they will brown.)
Watch and bake at 350° until done.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Dice celery, onion and green pepper; saute in butter.
Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Add to onion mixture.
Stir in chicken broth, milk and vegetable flakes.
Heat.
Add cheese; heat until hot, but do not boil.
Very good main course soup.

title: burger boat
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onions in a large nonstick skillet, stirring until beef crumbles.
Drain and return mixture to skillet.
Add soup and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.

title: "barbecue chicken with chips"
directions: Clean chicken (moist, damp).
Mix in bowl Shake 'N Bake seasoning with crushed barbecue chips.
Place chicken in mixture, then put in Pam sprayed casserole dish; with extra mixture, cover over chicken again.
Bake at low 250° to 300° (not high; will burn chips) for 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Spread 1 pkg. crescent rolls on small cookie sheet.
Mix together 1 egg yolk with 2 cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over crescent roll.
Spread the other pkg. crescent rolls on top of cream cheese mixture.
Whisk egg white and brush on top.
Then mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, broth, soups, Ro-Tel, onion, 1/2 pound cheese and bell pepper to form sauce.
Then in a 9 x 13-inch pan, tear tortillas into 4 or 5 pieces each and cover bottom of pan. Pour a thin layer of meat sauce on top.
Repeat tortilla layer and meat sauce layer.
Lightly season each layer of meat sauce with garlic salt and chili powder.
Top with remaining 1/2 pound of grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spice tea mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons for each cup of hot water.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Add onion and pepper and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add potatoes and cook for 8 minutes. Add eggs and stir and cook until eggs are done.
Prepare tortillas by heating in hot oil for 5 seconds on each side. Divide filling mixture between 12 tortillas, placing filling in center of each.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Fold over each side. Serve with picante sauce and sour cream.
These may be frozen and heated in microwave.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz.
Add cream of mushroom soup on top of stove. In separate pan, boil chicken until falls off bones or tender. Boil broccoli and rice until they are tender.
Pour off water and add to shredded chicken.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken pot pie
directions: Mix biscuit mix according to package directions for biscuits. Spray pie plate with Pam.
Pat 1/2 biscuit dough in bottom of pie plate.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour on top of biscuit dough. Put other 1/2 biscuit dough on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Contains 11 fat grams for entire pie.

title: pan-fried black bass
directions: Wipe the fish with a cloth dipped in lightly salted water, about 1 teaspoon of salt per quart of water.
Rub lightly with bacon drippings and roll thoroughly in corn meal.
Dust with a little salt and pepper into cavities.
Bacon drippings should be no less than 1/4-inch deep in the pan, no more than 1/2-inch deep and should be hot enough to brown a 1-inch cube of bread in 2 minutes, no hotter.
Cook until fish is nicely browned on one side, then turn and brown on other side.
Drain on paper before serving on heated plates.

title: turkey-potato skillet
directions: Cook onion in margarine until soft.
Stir in turkey, soup, salt and pepper; heat.
Fold in potatoes and heat.
Can substitute chicken for turkey.
Makes 4 servings.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Cut flour and shortening together.
Mix well and store in an airtight container.
Use this like you would use Bisquick; it's less expensive and works great.

title: casserole of plenty
directions: Mix
together
milk,
margarine,
cheese, bread crumbs, eggs, parsley, onion, pimiento, salt and pepper.	Combine with drained macaroni.
Pour
into
8-inch baking dish.	Place dish in a pan of water and bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Pound chicken pieces until very thin and double in size. Spread with Dijon and top with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Roll up chicken with inside and secure with a toothpick.
Dip into egg whites and roll in crumbs.
Brown briefly in sprayed nonstick pan. Place in an ovenproof dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.
Has 290 calories, less than 6 g fat.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Thaw strawberries enough to get juice off.
Dissolve Jell-O in juice.
Combine frozen berries and Jell-O; mix well.
Let congeal in refrigerator (not really firm).
Add milk to pudding; mix.
Add vanilla, sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Alternate layer of wafers, pudding and Jell-O mixture until all mixture is used.
Top with the rest of the Cool Whip.
This is pretty made in a clear glass bowl.

title: never fail oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs and other ingredients; mix well.
Drop on buttered cookie sheet.
Press flat.
Bake in slow oven at 325° about 15 minutes.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Mix sugar,
cornmeal and flour.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Beat well
after each, stir in butter, salt, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Mix	well,
pour
mixture
into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for
minutes
or
until
firm.	Cool before cutting. Serves 6.

title: bourbon pecan pie
directions: Soak pecans in bourbon overnight.
Combine eggs, sugar, Karo, salt,
chocolate chips, vanilla and pecans.
Pour
into 9-inch deep pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fried chicken fingers
directions: Cut
breast
in
finger
size strips.
Salt and pepper. Make a batter of Bisquick and sweet milk.
Dip the chicken in batter, covering each piece well.
Fry in deep fat (Crisco or Crisco oil). Drain on paper towels.

title: piggy rolls
directions: Mix pudding and brown sugar in bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon. Dip rolls in butter. Roll in sugar/pudding mixture.
Put in Bundt or angel food cake pan. Sprinkle with pecans and sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Pour remaining butter over rolls and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green and red salad
directions: Mix peas with celery, scallions and radishes.
Stir in mayonnaise and lemon juice to moisten and bind vegetables.
Cover and chill.
Serve in lettuce leaf cups.
Makes 10 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles.
Return drained noodles to kettle.
Saute mushrooms and onions about 3 minutes.
Add to noodles.
Stir in tuna, Cheddar cheese, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter; sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bova shaklet(german)
directions: Put potatoes and meat on dough.
Fold over half-way and pinch. Drop in boiling water and cook 15 minutes.
Serve with meat gravy over it or use cream sauce.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips, pour over cereal.
COOL.

title: hot rolls
directions: Use 1/2 cup milk to melt oleo to scald.
Cool slightly, then add to 1/2 cup milk and egg.
Add sugar and salt; mix.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix with milk and egg.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour.
Let rise in bowl until double.
Roll out mixture on floured board until 1 1/2 inches thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on cookie sheet and fold in half.
Let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until soft.
Add 5 whole eggs, one at a time.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla; beat until thin.
Pour into graham cracker crust (recipe follows).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool cake for 15 minutes.
Turn oven temperature down to 325°.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo, then add egg.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add sour milk to the egg mixture alternately with the flour mixture.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix sugar, Carnation milk and margarine.
After it begins to boil, boil 6 minutes.
Take off heat and blend in caramels.
Spread before it cools.

title: green eggs and ham(read the dr. suess story.)
directions: Heat oil.
Saute scallions, pepper and spinach.
Blend egg and milk and add to sauteed ingredients.
Stir until eggs are set. Add side piece of ham.

title: squash relish
directions: Let first 3 ingredients set overnight in refrigerator.
Rinse well; using colander.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grind 2 bell peppers.
Bring quickly to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Place in sterilized, hot pint jars and seal.
Makes 7 pints. This relish is great with meats and veggies.

title: zucchini texas hash
directions: Slice zucchini, onions and peppers; brown lightly in small amount oil, then set aside. Brown ground beef. Combine all ingredients in a casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until noodles are cooked. (Noodles will absorb fluid from vegetables.)

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Peel and chop garlic.
Add all ingredients, except potatoes, into bowl; mix well.
Add potatoes; toss to coat, then pour into ovenproof shallow casserole.
Roast potatoes for 30 to 40 minutes, until tender and browned.

title: savory oven pot roast
directions: Dust beef with combinations of seasonings and flour.
Heat oil in heavy ovenproof pan; brown meat, then remove.
Brown onions and garlic lightly in pan.
Replace meat; add remaining ingredients. Cover; bake at 350° until meat is tender, about 2 1/2 hours. Discard herb bouquet.
Serve with pan gravy.
Makes 10 servings.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir once or twice during first 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, then at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 small or 2 large loaves.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple cubes with sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add celery, nuts and grapes.
Gently fold in Miracle Whip.
Chill. Yield:
6 servings.

title: low calorie salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: fresh fried corn
directions: Heat frying pan with bacon drippings over medium heat; add cut corn and water.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Then add margarine; stir in flour and then sugar. Cover and simmer until ready to serve.

title: maple icing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Add syrup until icing is of right consistency.

title: chinese pork tenderloin
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate tenderloins for 1 to 2 hours, turning occasionally and keeping chilled.
Broil over a medium bed of charcoal, brushing with marinade before and after turning every 5 minutes, for a total of 25 minutes.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix flour, cocoa and salt; add to first mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallows evenly over cake, return to oven until they melt, about 10 minutes.
Let cool before icing.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: no name cake
directions: Bake cake in sheet pan according to pkg. directions.
While cake bakes, heat 1 large can crushed pineapple and 1 cup sugar. When cake is finished baking, take a large fork and make holes in cake.
Spread pineapple mixture over cake while hot.
Mix vanilla pudding according to pkg. directions.
After cake cools, spread pudding over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Decorate top with nuts and coconut.

title: chicken soup with barley
directions: In large pot, cook chicken in water until tender.
Cool broth and skim off fat.
Bone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces. Return to pot along with remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for at least 1 hour until vegetables and barley are tender. Remove bay leaf.
Serves 5.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: Butter a shallow 2-quart baking dish; set aside.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse under cold water.
Transfer to a large bowl and set aside.
Cook broccoli in lightly salted boiling water 5 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Mix in with noodles.
Add tuna and toss gently.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, about 7 minutes.
Stir in the cream, water, thickener, salt and pepper; cook until mixture boils and thickens, 5 to 8 minutes.
Pour sauce over noodle mixture and toss to combine.
Transfer to prepared baking dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until top is nicely browned and casserole is bubbly.
Let cool slightly before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Meanwhile, melt butter over low heat. Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk, stirring until sauce thickens. Add cheese and stir until melted. Add cooked, drained macaroni and mix. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Toss bread crumbs with melted butter and paprika. Sprinkle over top of macaroni. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Dissolve soda in warm water and add flour, spices, cocoa, vanilla and a little salt. Fold in apples and chopped nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 70 minutes in 350° oven.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together green beans, onion, chicken soup and mushroom soup in a long pan.
Bake for about 30 minutes, then put cheese on top and put back in for about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 9-inch glass pie plate. Pour refried beans on the cream cheese and then pour salsa onto beans. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden and bubbly. Serve with nachos.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Make into ball and roll in crushed English walnuts.

title: pink macaroni salad
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil, then add egg.
Stir until thickens slightly.
Boil orzo; drain.
Put in bowl, then add cherries, oranges and pineapple. Mix together.
Pour heated syrup mixture into macaroni and fruit.
After cooled, add Cool Whip and blend together.
The orzo noodles look like rice.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In a pot, melt margarine, sugar, and orange juice until fully dissolved.
Separate each crescent roll and press out with hand. Put one apple quarter into each roll and seal.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour sugar mixture over dumplings.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake until apples are tender and dumplings are brown.
